An Islamic Jihad military wing operative was killed in a fire exchange. A Border Police undercover officer was killed during the clashes.

Shot in the chest by Israeli forces during a fire exchange that broke after the forces entered the camp. His body was found in the early morning hours the next day. That day, Israeli forces killed 12 more Palestinians, six of them minors. Ten of the casualties were killed by a missile fired from an aircraft, including four minors and one al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative. A Border Police undercover officer was killed during the clashes. Ja'a'reh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft while standing in the street with other young men during a raid of the camp by Israeli armed forces. Nine other Palestinians were killed in the missile strike, including four minors and an al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative. Over the course of the day, two more Palestinian minors were fatally shot. An Islamic Jihad military wing operative was killed in a fire exchange. A Border Police undercover officer was killed during the clashes.

Shot in the head by soldiers while standing in his balcony during clashes that broke out between youths and soldiers who entered the camp to arrest workers from Gaza who were staying in one of the buildings. According to media reports, about 200 Gaza residents were arrested during the operation.
Injured by soldiers fire while throwing stones at a military tower and soldiers at the checkpoint along with other youths.
Fatally shot by soldiers while throwing stones at them during clashes that broke out at the checkpoint after a protest march against the Gaza war arrived from Nablus city center.
Shot in the chest by soldiers while running away from them after throwing stones with two other teens at military jeeps that were exiting Ramallah after arresting a Palestinian.
Fatally shot by soldiers while throwing stones at them along with other youths during clashes that broke out after the soldiers entered the camp and carried out a punitive house demolition.

Shot in the chest by soldiers while throwing stones at them along with other youths during clashes, which included explosive device throwing, that developed when the soldiers entered the village to arrest two Palestinians. Another Palestinian was killed by the soldiers' fire.

Fatally shot by soldiers while throwing stones at them along with other youths during clashes that developed when soldiers entered the village to arrest two Palestinians and included explosive device throwing. A minor was also killed by the soldiers' fire.

Killed by a missile strike while inside a mosque in the camp, which partially collapsed. An Islamic Jihad military wing operative was also killed in the incident. Abed was an al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative.

Killed by a missile strike while inside a mosque in the camp, which partially collapsed. An al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative was also killed in the incident. Abdallah was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.
Shot in the chest and thighs by Israeli forces while throwing stones during clashes that broke out after soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet entered the camp and arrested a Palestinian.

Fatally shot by soldiers from a distance of about 70 meters while fleeing them on foot, after striking a soldier with his car as he tried to drive around a roadblock the military set up at the exit from the camp. Israel is holding his body.
Shot in the back by soldiers while throwing stones at military jeeps that entered the town during clashes that included fire exchanges with armed Palestinian.

Shot in the head while throwing stones at joint military, Border Police and Shin Bet force as it was leaving the city of Tubas after clashes that broke out when the force made arrests and included fire exchanges. Bani Odeh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Fatally shot from a military jeep while throwing stones from a distance of 40 meters, with other youths, at the convoy of which the jeep was part as it was exiting the camp after a joint military, Border Police and Shin Beit raid on the camp in which 15 Palestinians were arrested. Another Palestinian who tried to evacuate Alian was killed by the forces gunfire. The military claims explosive devices and blocks were thrown at the forces during the incident.

Fatally shot from a military jeep during the retreat of joint military, Border Police and Shin Beit force that entered the camp and arrested 15 Palestinians. Shot while helping to evacuate an injured man who later dies of his wounds. Nakhleh threw stones at the military jeeps earlier. The military claims explosive devices and blocks were thrown at the forces during the incident.

Wounded from shots fired by a settler while riding in a car with two other young men who were wounded in the shooting. The settler claimed he heard a sound resembling gunfire from the direction of their car.

Fatally shot by soldiers while watching from the roof of his house together with relatives as Israeli forces left the camp after arresting 14 Palestinians. According to the military, while the Israeli forces operated in the camp, youths threw explosive devices and blocks at them and burned tires. Mteir's evacuation for medical treatment was delayed for about 15 minutes because the Israeli forces blocked the exit from the camp.
Wounded in the thigh from shots fired by a soldier who came out of a jeep as al-Fuqahaa was fleeing after throwing stones and military jeeps that drove through the village.
Shot in the chest by soldiers and Border Police officers who entered the town and arrested residents. Nazzal was throwing stones at the forces, along with other youths.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft while throwing explosive devices at Israeli forces during clashes that broke out following their incursion into the camp and the arrest of Palestinians. Abu Qutneh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Three other Palestinians, including two minors, one of them an Islamic Jihad military wing operative, were killed in the incident.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft while throwing explosive devices at Israeli forces during clashes that broke out following their incursion into the camp and the arrest of Palestinians. Sabah was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Three other Palestinians, including two Islamic Jihad military wing operatives, one of them a minor, and another minor were killed in the incident.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft while throwing explosive devices at Israeli forces during clashes that broke out following their incursion into the camp and the arrest of Palestinians. Three Islamic Jihad military wing operatives were killed in the incident, including two minors.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft while throwing explosive devices at Israeli forces during clashes that broke out following their incursion into the camp and the arrest of Palestinians. Al-Fayed was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Three minors were killed in the incident, including two other Islamic Jihad military wing operatives.

Shot in the abdomen by soldiers while throwing stones at them along with other youths during clashes that broke out when the soldiers entered the camp to close a gate installed by the military that cuts off the home of an extended family from the camp. The settlement of Beit El was built near the home. The soldiers later shot another minor, wounding him.

Shot in the back and chest by Israeli forces after throwing stones at them during clashes, which included fire exchanges, that broke out after soldiers and undercover Border Police officers entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. Two armed men, including a senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative were killed in the fire exchange.

Fatally shot while firing at soldiers during a fire exchange that broke out after soldiers and undercover Border Police officers entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. Another armed man and a minor who threw an explosive device were also killed in the fire exchange. Al-'Amer was a senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Shot in the chest while firing at soldiers during a fire exchange that broke out after soldiers and undercover Border Police officers entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. A senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative and a minor who threw an explosive device were also killed in the fire exchange.

A muezzin at al-Fatah mosque. Shot in the chest by soldiers while leaving the mosque during morning prayers to move his motorbike, after he heard armed Palestinians in the area shooting at soldiers. The soldiers entered the city to demolish a shop as punishment and to arrest a Palestinian.
Fatally shot by a soldier in plainclothes who arrived with settlers at Salehs family olive grove and tried to drive out family members who were harvesting olives.

Shot in the abdomen by soldiers and Border Police officers as he emerged from behind a street corner while the forces were carrying out a punitive house demolition. During the demolition, clashes broke out involving stone-throwing tire-burning, throwing of explosive devices and shots fired at the forces. Clashes also broke out in the nearby Balata R.C., during which another Palestinian was killed and two were injured.

Wounded by gunfire shot by soldiers and Border Police while clashing with them along with other youths after the forces entered the city and, according to media reports, arrested four Palestinians. According to the military, during the clashes the Palestinians threw explosives at the forces and exchanged fire with them.
Fatally shot by soldiers and Border Police officers while throwing stones at them from a roof during clashes that broke out after the forces entered the camp and arrested a Palestinian.

Shot in the abdomen by soldiers who emerged from an ambush while he was watching tracking the movement of military jeeps along with other youths and advancing towards them. The soldiers wounded 11 other youths who were with him. According to the military, Palestinians threw Molotov cocktails and explosive devices at the soldiers.

Shot in the thighs by Israeli forces while throwing stones at them during clashes, which included fire exchanges, that broke out after Border Police, soldiers and Shin Bet entered the town and arrested Palestinians. Three more Palestinians were injured in the incident.

Shot in the abdomen by soldiers and Border Police officers while driving two other military wing operatives, who were injured, after they fired at the forces during their incursion into the camp area. The clashes broke out following a punitive house demolition in Askar R.C., where Israeli forces killed another Palestinian. The clashes in Balatah included stones and explosive devices being thrown at security forces. Died of his wounds shortly after. 'Arafat was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Wounded in the head from shots fired by soldiers at whom Palestinian youths were throwing stones, while driving by with his uncle. His uncle was lightly injured by the gunfire. A minor who was about to throw a stone at one of the jeeps passing through the area was injured during the clashes and died of his injuries on 31 October 2023.

Wounded in the buttock and leg by shots fired by soldiers in ambush as he was about to throw a stone at a military jeep that was passing by, near the site of clashes between the soldiers and the Palestinians. Two other Palestinians who were driving by were injured in the incident, including a minor who died of his injuries on 2 November 2023.

Killed by a missile strike while participating in clashes that included fire exchanges and explosive device throwing during an incursion into the camp by soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet. Three armed Palestinians were killed in the fire exchange, including two other Islamic Jihad military wing operatives.

Fatally shot by Border Police officers at the end of a short chase on foot after he stabbed a Border Police officer. According to media reports, the officer was severely wounded. Israel is holding his body.
A man with an intellectual disability. Shot in the neck by soldiers while throwing stones at them along with other youths who retreated in the meantime.

Wounded in the shoulder and arm while participating in fire exchanges that developed between armed Palestinians and military, Border Police and Shin Bet forces after the forces entered the camp. Two Islamic Jihad military wing operatives were also fatally shot during a fire exchange and an armed Palestinian minor was killed by a missile strike. Shurbaji died shortly after.

Killed in a fire exchange that developed between armed Palestinians and military, Border Police and Shin Bet forces that entered the camp. Two other armed Palestinians were killed in fire exchanges during the incident, an Islamic Jihad military wing operative and another armed operative. An armed Palestinian minor was killed by a missile strike.

Wounded in the back while participating in fire exchanges that developed between armed Palestinians and military, Border Police and Shin Bet forces after the forces entered the camp. A another Islamic Jihad military wing operative and another armed Palestinian were also killed in the fire exchange. An armed Palestinian minor was killed by a missile strike. Ba'jawi died a short while later.

Shot in the head by Israeli forces while sitting at the entrance to a store during clashes, which included fire exchanges, that broke out after the forces entered the city and arrested five Palestinians. At least nine more Palestinians were injured by the soldiers' fire.

Shot in the chest by soldiers who were standing on the roof of a house while throwing stones at soldiers on the ground along with other youths during clashes that developed after a demonstration against the war in Gaza.

Wounded in the back by soldiers fire while standing on the street in the center of the village with other youths, during the soldiers incursion into the village. Several residents threw stones at the soldiers. Another youth was injured by soldiers gunfire in the western part of the village.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft while participating in a fire exchange with soldiers and Border Police officers who had entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. Two more Palestinians, both members of the Palestinian Authority security forces were killed in the incident, while participating in the fire exchange. One was killed by a firearm and the other by the missile.

Member of the Palestinian Authority security forces. Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft while participating in a fire exchange with soldiers and Border Police officers who had entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. Two more Palestinians who participated in the fire exchange, one of them a member of the Palestinian Authority security forces, were also killed, one by a firearm and the other by the missile.

Member of the Palestinian Authority security forces. Shot in the head while participating in a fire exchange with soldiers and Border Police officers who had entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. Two more Palestinians who participated in the fire exchange, one of them a member of the Palestinian Authority security forces, were killed by a missile fired from an aircraft.
A man with an intellectual disability. Shot in the upper body by Israeli forces while walking in the street after the Israeli forces entered the city and arrested a Palestinian.
Fatally shot by Palestinians from a car that overtook his car on Route 557.

Shot in the chest by soldiers while trying to find cover after throwing stones at them with other teens as the soldiers were retreating from the city after arresting three Palestinians. Two other Palestinians were wounded by soldier fire during the clashes and another Palestinian who was watching the clashes was fatally shot.

Fatally shot by soldiers while watching clashes that broke out during their retreat from the city, after arresting three Palestinians. One minor was killed by soldier fire during clashes in the area and two other Palestinians were wounded.

Shot in the chest and abdomen by soldiers, along with another armed Palestinian during a fire exchange that broke out after the Israeli forces entered the camp and arrested a Palestinian. Several hours later, another Palestinian was fatally shot while standing on the balcony of his house watching the military jeeps leaving the camp. Two Islamic Jihad military wing operatives, one of them a minor and the other a Palestinian citizen of Israel, were killed by a missile strike.

Fatally shot by soldiers along with another armed Palestinian, during a fire exchange that broke out after the Israeli forces entered the camp and arrested a Palestinian. Several hours later, another Palestinian was fatally shot while standing on the balcony of his house watching the military jeeps leaving the camp. Two Islamic Jihad military wing operatives, one of them a minor and the other a Palestinian citizen of Israel, were killed by a missile strike.

Shot in the head by Israeli forces while throwing stones at them during clashes that broke out after they entered the camp and included gunfire. According to the Palestinian Ministry of Health, two more Palestinians, one of them a minor, were injured by the Israeli forces' fire.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft while participating in a fire exchange with soldiers who had entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. Another Islamic Jihad military wing operative, a Palestinian citizen of Israel, was also killed by a missile. A few hours earlier, the soldiers killed two other armed men. Another Palestinian who was standing on the balcony of his house watching the military jeeps leaving the camp was fatally shot in the city of Jenin.
Fatally shot by soldiers when throwing stones at them during clashes that broke out following a protest against the Gaza war.
Fatally shot by soldiers at a checkpoint, after, according to the military, speeding towards them on his car and then getting out of it holding a knife. Israel is holding his body.
Wounded by soldiers gunfire while standing on his balcony during their withdrawal from the town after arresting Palestinians.
Fatally shot by soldiers when leaving Friday prayers at the mosque along with other Palestinians, some of whom threw stones at soldiers who had entered the village shortly before.

Member of the Palestinian Authority security forces. Fatally shot by a soldier or a Border Police officer from the balcony of a nearby building, while standing on his rooftop with his brother, watching Israeli forces exit the camp after confiscating equipment from a lathe. During the clashes that developed in the area, Palestinians threw stones and Molotov cocktails and the Israeli forces shot and wounded 12 Palestinians. One of the wounded men, who did not participate in the clashes, died of his wounds shortly after.

Wounded by soldiers or Border Police officers, while on the street during clashes that broke out after the Israeli forces entered homes in the camp, as well as a lathe, from which they confiscated equipment. Died of his wounds shortly after. During the clashes, Palestinians threw stones and Molotov cocktails at the Israeli forces. Eleven more Palestinians were wounded by the gunfire and a member of the Palestinian Authority security forces was killed while watching the forces retreat from the roof of his house.

Shot in the head by soldiers while standing on the balcony of his house watching military jeeps leaving Jenin R.C. after soldiers arrested a Palestinian there. Several hours earlier, two Palestinians were fatally shot during a fire exchange with soldiers, and two Islamic Jihad military wing operatives, one a minor and one a Palestinian citizen of Israel, were killed by a missile fired from an Israeli aircraft.

Shot in the back by Border Police officers when trying to flee them after advancing towards them in the street together with other youths, some of whom threw stones. Most of the soldiers and officers had already retreated from the camp by then. The forces entered the camp to seal a printing press as a punitive measure and arrest Palestinians.

Wounded by soldiers fire while throwing stones at them along with other youths as the soldiers withdrew from the village after arresting workers from Gaza who had been there since the war broke out. Died of his wounds shortly after. Two other youths were injured in the shooting.

Fatally shot by soldiers and Border Police officers in a street near a house where he barricaded himself and where, a short time before, a Hamas military wing operative was fatally shot. Another Palestinian was fatally shot when he tried to evacuate a wounded man. During clashes that broke out in the area, Palestinians threw stones and improvised explosive devices at the Israeli forces.

Fatally shot by soldiers and Border Police officers who surrounded a house he barricaded himself in. An exchange of fire developed between Halabiyah and the Israeli forces, during which the forces fired an anti-tank missile at the house. A Palestinian present near the house and another Palestinian who tried to evacuate an injured person there, were fatally shot by the Israeli forces. During clashes that broke out in the area, Palestinians threw stones and improvised explosive devices at the Israeli forces. Halabiyah was a Hamas military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.
Critically wounded when a Palestinian minor stabbed her and another police officer who was lightly wounded. The stabber was fatally shot by Border Police officers.
Wounded by soldiers' fire while participating in clashes during which Palestinians threw stones and launched fireworks at the soldiers after they entered the village. Died a short while later.

Fatally shot by members of the Special Police Unit and the Shin Bet while riding in a car with three other men, all of whom were al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operatives. One was a senior operative and another was a Palestinian citizen of Israel. All three were also killed. 'Awwad was a senior Hamas military wing operative.

Fatally shot by members of the Special Police Unit and the Shin Bet while riding in a car with three other men, one a senior Hamas military wing operative and two al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operatives, one of whom was a Palestinian citizen of Israel. All three were also killed. Shhadeh was a senior al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative.

Fatally shot by members of the Special Police Unit and the Shin Bet while riding in a car with three other men, one a senior Hamas military wing operative, one a senior al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative, and another al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative who was a Palestinian citizen of Israel. All three were also killed. Rajab was an al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative.
Fatally shot by soldiers while near the separation fence officers with other youths. His body was found shortly after.

Fatally shot by Border Police officers after stabbing two of them, critically wounding one and lightly wounding another. The critically wounded officer died of her injuries later that day. Israel is holding his body.

Wounded by Israeli forces gunfire while participating in clashes that included stone-throwing and broke out after soldiers entered homes in the town and arrested Palestinians. Died of his wounds shortly after. According to media reports, at least five more Palestinians were wounded by the Israeli forces fire in the clashes.

Wounded by Israeli forces fire while throwing stones at them along with other youths while the soldiers were surveying a house designated for punitive demolition. Died a short while later. According to the military, the youths threw Molotov cocktails at the forces. Two other youths were injured in the shooting.

Wounded by soldiers gunfire while standing in the street, watching clashes that broke out after the soldiers entered the city and surrounded a house to arrest a Palestinian. The Palestinian turned himself in to the forces the next day, after his family members were detained at home for several hours.

Shot in the abdomen by Border Police officers while walking down the street on his way to work after the officers and soldiers entered the camp and arrested two Palestinians. Five other bystanders and a resident who was standing on the roof of his house were injured by the Israeli forces' fire. Died of his wounds shortly after.

Wounded by Israeli forces gunfire while throwing stones at them during clashes that broke out after they entered the camp. Died of his wounds shortly after. Palestinians fired and threw stones at Israeli forces during the clashes. According to media reports, 17 more Palestinians were injured by the Israeli forces' fire.

Wounded by Israeli forces gunfire while on his rooftop during clashes that broke out after soldiers and Border Police officers entered the camp and arrested seven Palestinians. Soldiers stopped his father's car on its way to take him to a hospital and arrested him, injured. The military soon after notified the family their son had died of his wounds and his body was handed over to them later that morning at the a-Nashash checkpoint. The military claims that during operations in Ayidah R.C. and a-Duheisheh R.C. that day, Palestinians threw Molotov cocktails and explosive devices at the soldiers.

Wounded by Israeli soldiers gunfire while throwing stones at them along with other youths during clashes that broke out after the soldiers entered the village. Died of his wounds shortly after. According to media reports, two more Palestinians were wounded in the shooting. The media also reported that the soldiers went to the village after a shooting incident nearby in which two settlers were injured and that they entered several homes and confiscated a security camera.
Shot in the neck by soldiers while trying to cross the separation fence and enter Israel to look for work.

According to media reports, a soldier was severely wounded by shots fired by armed Palestinians during the clashes.

Fatally shot by Israeli forces during clashes, in which he participated from a rooftop, that developed after soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet personnel raided the camp and the city of Tulkarm.During the raid, which lasted about two days, the forces arrested at least seven Palestinians and killed seven others in the city and the refugee camp. Four of the dead, including three minors, were killed by a missile fired from an aircraft. Three other Palestinians were killed during the clashes; one had thrown an explosive device at the Israeli forces; another drove through the area where the clashes were taking place and the third was standing on a rooftop watching the clashes. According to media reports, a soldier was severely wounded by shots fired by armed Palestinians during the clashes. Salit was a Hamas military wing operative.

Killed along with three other Palestinians, all minors, by a missile fired from an aircraft when they were near armed Palestinians who fired and threw explosive devices at soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet personnel who raided the camp and the city of Tulkarm. During the raid, which lasted about two days, the forces arrested at least seven Palestinians and killed four others in the city and the refugee camp, including a Hamas military wing operative, who was shot during a fire exchange, a Palestinian who was standing on his rooftop watching the clashes that developed following the raid, a Palestinian who threw an explosive device during the clashes, and a Palestinian who drove through the area where the clashes were taking place. According to media reports, a soldier was severely wounded by shots fired by armed Palestinians during the clashes.

Killed along with three other Palestinians, including two other minors, by a missile fired from an aircraft when they were near armed Palestinians who fired and threw explosive devices at soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet personnel who raided the camp and the city of Tulkarm. During the raid, which lasted about two days, the forces arrested at least seven Palestinians and killed four others in the city and the refugee camp, including a Hamas military wing operative, who was shot during a fire exchange, a Palestinian who was standing on his rooftop watching the clashes that developed following the raid, a Palestinian who threw an explosive device during the clashes, and a Palestinian who drove through the area where the clashes were taking place. According to media reports, a soldier was severely wounded by shots fired by armed Palestinians during the clashes.

Killed along with three other Palestinians, including two other minors, by a missile fired from an aircraft when they were near armed Palestinians who fired and threw explosive devices at soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet personnel who raided the camp and the city of Tulkarm. During the raid, which lasted about two days, the forces arrested at least seven Palestinians and killed four others in the city and the refugee camp, including a Hamas military wing operative, who was shot during a fire exchange, a Palestinian who was standing on his rooftop watching the clashes that developed following the raid, a Palestinian who threw an explosive device during the clashes, and a Palestinian who drove through the area where the clashes were taking place. According to media reports, a soldier was severely wounded by shots fired by armed Palestinians during the clashes.

Killed along with three other Palestinians, including two other minors, by a missile fired from an aircraft when they were near armed Palestinians who fired and threw explosive devices at soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet personnel who raided the camp and the city of Tulkarm. During the raid, which lasted about two days, the forces arrested at least seven Palestinians and killed four others in the city and the refugee camp, including a Hamas military wing operative, who was shot during a fire exchange, a Palestinian who was standing on his rooftop watching the clashes that developed following the raid, a Palestinian who threw an explosive device during the clashes, and a Palestinian who drove through the area where the clashes were taking place. According to media reports, a soldier was severely wounded by shots fired by armed Palestinians during the clashes.

Fatally shot by Israeli forces while standing on a rooftop, watching clashes that developed after soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet personnel raided the camp and the city of Tulkarm. During the raid, which lasted about two days, the forces arrested at least seven Palestinians and killed seven others in the city and the refugee camp. Four of the dead, including three minors, were killed by a missile fired from an aircraft. A Hamas military wing operative was also killed in a fire exchange and two Palestinians were killed in clashes that developed following the raid, during which Palestinians threw explosive devices and fired at the Israeli forces. One of the two had thrown an explosive device at the Israeli forces and the other drove through the area where the clashes were taking place. According to media reports, a soldier was severely wounded by shots fired by armed Palestinians during the clashes.

Fatally shot by Israeli forces after a short chase on foot that followed him throwing an explosive device at them, during clashes that developed after the Israeli forces raided the city of Tulkarm and the refugee camp. Palestinians fired at Israeli forces during the clashes. The forces chased Othman to the entrance of a house and shot him there. His body was found with his feet tied.During the raid, which lasted about two days, the forces arrested at least seven Palestinians and killed seven others in the city and the refugee camp. Four of the dead, including three minors, were killed by a missile fired from an aircraft. A Hamas military wing operative was also killed in a fire exchange and two Palestinians were killed in the clashes. One of the two was standing on a rooftop watching the clashes, and the other drove through the area where the clashes were taking place. According to media reports, a soldier was severely wounded by shots fired by armed Palestinians during the clashes.

A Palestinian with US citizenship. Shot in the head by an off-duty Israel Police officer and an Israeli citizen while riding in his car with his friend, a minor, on his family's land near the village. According to the military, the shooting, carried out in the presence of a soldier, was prompted by suspicions that the minors threw stones at Route 60. BTselems investigation reveals that the two were shot as they were about to head back after an excursion on land owned by Ajaqs family and did not pose a threat to anyone. After the shooting, two military jeeps arrived at the scene, and then more shots were fired at Ajaqs car.

Wounded by Israeli forces gunfire when he and several other Palestinians stood behind a dumpster, watching, from about 70 meters away, the movements of an armed forces contingent that went into the home of a detainee from the village and confiscated a car. BTselems research revealed that when the forces first arrived at the village, a handful of stones were thrown at them, but no clashes were underway at the time Kharmah was shot. After Kharmah was injured, some youths threw stones at the armed forces and set dumpsters on fire.
Shot in the abdomen by soldiers when throwing stones at them during clashes in which other Palestinians threw improvised explosive devices at the soldiers.

Shot in the head and upper body by soldiers, after, according to the soldiers, riding up to the checkpoint on a scooter and firing at them. Ayesh was a Hamas military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.
Shot all over his body while at home with members of his family by undercover Border Police officers who surrounded the house and arrested his brother. Khashan was a Hamas military wing operative.
Wounded in the abdomen by Israeli forces gunfire while participating in a fire exchange that broke out after they entered the camp. Yasin was an al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative.

Wounded by Israeli forces gunfire while participating in clashes that lasted several hours and during which youths threw stones at Israeli forces that entered the town, raided homes and played soccer in the field. Died of his wounds shortly after. Four more Palestinians were wounded by the Israeli forces gunfire. One of them died of his wounds later that day.

Injured in the head while chasing military jeeps that were retreating from the town after Israeli forces raided it, entered homes and played soccer in the field. Died of his wounds shortly after. In clashes that developed after the soldiers entered, Palestinians threw stones at the soldiers, who fired and wounded four of them. One of the wounded died of his wounds that day.

Fatally shot by a police officer from a jeep, from about 100 meters away, while walking home from school. Hamed was shot on the street, near the hiding spot of some youths who, shortly before, threw stones at Israel Police, Border Police and military forces that entered the city. The Israeli forces were roaming the streets of the town, shouting provocations on a loudspeaker, stopping residents and passersby and firing tear gas. The police claimed Hamed threw a Molotov cocktail at the Israeli forces.

Fatally shot by soldiers who had entered the town and arrested Palestinians, while walking down the street. Security camera footage shows Hamu walking down the street, not carrying a weapon, and then running, sustaining a gunshot wound and falling to the ground. During clashes that broke out in the town, Palestinians threw stones and improvised explosive devices and fired at the soldiers. According to the military, the soldiers fired at Hamu after he fired at soldiers who tried to stop him.
Fatally shot by soldiers who claimed he had approached a military post holding a knife. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot with his brother and their friend, by Special Police Unit and Shin Bet personnel in his room at Ibn Sina Hospital, where he was hospitalized after being injured by fragments from an Israeli missile on 25 October 2023. Both brothers were Islamic Jihad military wing operatives and the friend was a Hamas military wing operative. The Israeli personnel, who entered the hospital disguised as medical staff and Palestinian visitors, attacked some of the staff on their way in.

Fatally shot with his brother and their friend, by Special Police Unit and Shin Bet personnel in a room at Ibn Sina Hospital, where the brother, also an Islamic Jihad military wing operative, was hospitalized after being injured by fragments from an Israeli missile on 25 October 2023. The friend was a Hamas military wing operative. The Israeli personnel, who entered the hospital disguised as medical staff and Palestinian visitors, attacked some of the staff on their way in.

Fatally shot with two brothers, both Islamic Jihad military wing operatives, by Special Police Unit and Shin Bet personnel in a room at Ibn Sina Hospital, where one of the brothers was hospitalized after being injured by fragments from an Israeli missile on 25 October 2023. The Israeli personnel, who entered the hospital disguised as medical staff and Palestinian visitors, attacked some of the staff on their way in. Jalamneh was a Hamas military wing operative.

Fatally shot by Border Police officers while fleeing them after attempting to stab one of them when the two officers were standing on the road next to their vehicle. Security camera footage shows the officers firing at Alian as he lies wounded on the ground. Israel is holding his body.
Fatally shot by soldiers at a checkpoint after, according to the army, having advanced towards them carrying weapons. Israel is holding his body.

Killed while barricaded in his house during a fire exchange with soldiers and Border Police officers. A bulldozer destroyed parts of the building, and then the Israeli forces fired anti-tank missiles at it. During a fire exchange in the homes yard, two other Palestinians, both al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operatives, were also killed. One was Alis cousin and the other was also an officer with the Palestinian Authority security forces. According to the military, they were shot while trying to escape. According to the Palestinian Red Crescent Society, nine others were wounded by the Israeli forces fire. Israel is holding the body of Hussein Ali, who was a senior al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative.

Shot by soldiers and Border Police undercover officers, who fired at him, along with another al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative, who was also an officer with the Palestinian Authority security forces, during a fire exchange with the Israeli forces in the yard of a building where his cousin, a senior operative in the Brigade, who was also killed, was barricaded. According to the military, the two were shot while trying to escape. According to the Palestinian Red Crescent Society, nine others were wounded by the Israeli forces fire.

An officer with the Palestinian Authority security forces. Shot by soldiers and Border Police undercover officers, who fired at him, along with another al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative, during a fire exchange with the Israeli forces in the yard of a building where a senior operative in the Brigade, who was also killed, was barricaded. According to the military, the two were shot while trying to escape. According to the Palestinian Red Crescent Society, nine others were wounded by the Israeli forces fire.
Fatally shot by soldiers at a checkpoint after, according to the military, firing at them and hitting the helmet of one. Israel is holding his body.

Wounded by soldiers gunfire while throwing stones at them along with other youths after the soldiers entered the town. While in the town, the soldiers shot and wounded two other youths and arrested two others. Died of his wounds shortly after.

A Palestinian with US citizenship. Shot in the head by Israeli armed forces who were on the other side of the separation fence while driving home with a friend who is a minor from a hike in woods located about 100-150 meters from the separation barrier. The friend fled on foot to a nearby village and returned to the car with some youths who helped him take al-Khaddur to an ambulance that was waiting for them. He was pronounced dead at the hospital.

Fatally shot by soldiers while on his way home, located 50 meters away. The military claims he was shot after trying to stab one of the soldiers. An eyewitness told BTselem Bataha was shot after an argument between him and the soldiers.
Wounded by Border Police officers fire after, according to the police, trying to stab them on al-Wad (HaGuy) Street. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot by Israeli armed forces while driving in his car during a raid of the camp by military, Border Police and Shin Bet forces, during which they arrested seven Palestinians. According to the military, Silmi tried to run over security personnel who were in the street.

Wounded in the head by shots fired by soldiers and Border Police officers who entered the town when school let out and students threw stones at the Israeli forces. Died of his wounds shortly after. According to media reports, 18 more Palestinians were wounded by the Israeli forces' fire, at least nine of them minors. 11 were wounded by live fire and seven by rubber coated metal bullets.

Fatally shot along with an Israeli soldier by an armed Palestinian who opened fire at Israelis in Reem (Masmiya) Junction. The shooter was fatally shot by a soldier. According to media reports, four other Israelis were wounded in the shooting, one critically and another severely.

Fatally shot along with an Israeli citizen by an armed Palestinian who opened fire at Israelis in Reem (Masmiya) Junction. The shooter was fatally shot by a soldier. According to media reports, four other Israelis were wounded in the shooting, one critically and another severely.

Fatally shot by a soldier after opening fire at Israelis at Reem (Masmiya) Junction, killing a civilian and a soldier and wounding four other Israelis, who according to the media, sustained critical or severe injuries. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot during a fire exchange with soldiers and Border Police officers who surrounded the house where he was barricaded. Clashes broke out following the Israeli forces incursion into the camp, during which Palestinians fired at them. Al-Ofi was an al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative. Another Palestinian was shot while standing on his rooftop in the camp. Israel is holding al-Ofis body. According to the police, an undercover Border Police officer was severely injured in the shooting.

Wounded in the back of the head by Israeli forces gunfire while standing on the roof of his familys building together with several siblings and cousins, as the forces entered the camp and surrounded another home, where an al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative was barricaded. The Israeli forces killed the operative during a fire exchange. Amers family members carried him to an ambulance that was waiting 200 meters away from the building because the driver was afraid to get closer due to the Israeli forces actions.

Member of the Palestinian Authority security forces. Shot by soldiers when he drove up to the Beit Furik checkpoint, according to the military, after failing to heed the soldiers calls. According to his family, Dweikat suffered from a psychosocial disability.

Shot in the shoulder by soldiers while on the street throwing stones at them from a rooftop. The soldiers entered the town after some youths threw an improvised explosive device at Route 55. After the shooting, the soldiers prevented his evacuation for at least half an hour. Died of his wounds shortly after.

Fatally shot during a fire exchange with soldiers and Border Police officers who entered the camp. During the clashes that developed after they entered, Palestinians fired and threw stones and explosive devices at the Israeli forces. 14 Palestinians were arrested during the raid. Ali was an al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative.

Fatally shot near a-Zaayem Checkpoint by three armed Palestinians who came out of two cars and opened fire at Israeli passengers. Eight other Israelis were wounded by the gunfire. Two of the shooters were fatally shot by Israeli officers and civilians and the third was wounded and arrested.

killed by a missile fired from an aircraft while traveling by car in the center of the camp. 17 other Palestinians who were on the street were wounded by the gunfire, including a minor who died of his wounds soon after and an Islamic Jihad military wing operative who died of his wounds on 26 February 2024. Hanun was a senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Wounded on the street by a missile fired from an aircraft at a car in which a senior Islamic Jihad operative was traveling. The operative died on the spot. 16 other Palestinians were wounded by the gunfire, including an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Died of his wounds on 26 February 2024.

Wounded on the street by a missile fired from an aircraft at a car in which a senior Islamic Jihad operative was traveling. The operative died on the spot. 16 other Palestinians were wounded by the gunfire, including a minor who died of his wounds soon after. Nabahnah was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Fatally shot with another Palestinian by Israeli civilians and police officers. The two were shot after firing at Israeli passengers near a-Zaayem Checkpoint, killing one and wounding eight. Another shooter was wounded and arrested. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot with another Palestinian by Israeli civilians and police officers. The two were shot after firing at Israeli passengers near a-Zaayem Checkpoint, killing one and wounding eight. His brother, who took part in the shooting, was wounded and arrested. Israel is holding his body.

Shot in the chest by Border Police officers gunfire while climbing the separation fence between his town and the Zur Baher neighborhood of East Jerusalem with his brother. Died of his wounds shortly after.

Shot in the head, chest, shoulder and leg by soldiers while participating, along with other Palestinians, in a fire exchange with soldiers who entered the city with Shin Bet personnel. During the raid, two more Palestinians were killed by the Israeli forces fire in the nearby al-Farah R.C. One was killed while throwing an explosive device and the other while standing by his window. The military claimed he participated in the clashes. Daraghmeh was a senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative. According to media reports, three more Palestinians were injured by the Israeli forces fire in the city and a soldier was lightly wounded.

Shot in the chest by Israeli forces while throwing an improvised explosive device at them during clashes that developed after military and Shin Bet forces entered the camp. His cousin, who was standing at his window was also killed by the Israeli forces fire. The military claimed he participated in the clashes. A senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative was killed during a fire exchange with soldiers in the nearby city of Tubas. According to media reports, three more Palestinians were injured by the Israeli forces fire in the city and a soldier was lightly wounded.

Shot in the head by Israeli forces while looking at the street from his window, shortly after his cousin was killed by the Israeli forces while throwing an improvised explosive device at them during clashes that developed after military and Shin Bet forces entered the camp. According to the army, Bayadsah participated in the clashes. Soldiers killed a senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative in the nearby city of Tubas during a fire exchange. According to media reports, three more Palestinians were injured by the Israeli forces fire in the city and a soldier was lightly wounded.
Fatally shot along with another Israeli civilian by a Palestinian Authority police officer who opened fire at Israelis at a gas station in the settlement. The shooter was fatally shot by a soldier.
Fatally shot along with an Israeli minor by a Palestinian Authority police officer who opened fire at Israelis at a gas station in the settlement. The shooter was fatally shot by a soldier.
A Palestinian Authority police officer. Fatally shot by a soldier after opening fire at Israeli civilians at a gas station in the settlement and killing two of them. Israel is holding his body.

Shot in the chest, abdomen and left arm and leg by soldiers in ambush while trying to climb the separation fence to return to the West Bank with his two brothers. The brothers had been picking aqub (gundelia) for several days. His two brothers were also wounded, and one of them died of his wounds soon after. The third brother was detained for several hours and then released. A fourth brother, who remained in Israel and continued picking aqub, tried to return home via Tarqumya Checkpoint after hearing his brothers had been shot. He was detained at the checkpoint and sent to administrative detention.

Shot in the chest by soldiers in ambush while trying to climb the separation fence to return to the West Bank with his two brothers. The brothers had been picking aqub (gundelia) for several days. His two brothers were also wounded, and one of them died of his wounds soon after. The third brother was detained for several hours and then released. A fourth brother, who remained in Israel and continued picking aqub, tried to return home via Tarqumya Checkpoint after hearing his brothers had been shot. He was detained at the checkpoint and sent to administrative detention.
Wounded by Israeli soldiers gunfire while throwing stones at them along with other youths as the soldiers were entering the village.

Wounded by Israeli forces gunfire while participating in clashes that developed after they entered the camp and arrested a Palestinian. During the clashes, Palestinians threw stones and improvised explosive devices at the Israeli forces and fired at them.

Wounded in the head by shots fired by soldiers in ambush, while standing and talking to his brother and another minor, on their way home, thinking the military had withdrawn from the village. Earlier, Palestinian youths gathered and some of them threw stones at military jeeps that entered the village and drove around in it. The soldiers prevented Ghneims evacuation for several minutes. Died of his wounds shortly after.

Fatally shot by soldiers from inside the settlement of Beit El. According to a friend who was with him and was injured by fragments, the two were sitting near the fence. According to the military, Zeid was shot after he threw a Molotov cocktail into the area of the settlement. The military held his body for about an hour, and then left it on the ground and notified the Palestinian DCO about its location.

Wounded by soldiers gunfire on the way home from work. Some youths threw stones at the soldiers, who had entered the village in three jeeps, fired live rounds, and hit a 10-year-old child who was traveling in a car with his father and brother in the head. The soldiers also assaulted three Palestinians, including a minor, and arrested another minor.

Wounded by soldiers gunfire, while traveling in a car with his father and younger brother. Some youths threw stones at the soldiers, who entered the village in three military jeeps, and responded with gunfire that hit a-Najar. The soldiers held up the car in which residents tried to take him to get medical treatment, and he died shortly after. During their incursion into the village, the soldiers shot and wounded another youth, who died on 7 March 2024, assaulted three other residents, including a minor, and arrested a minor.

Wounded by shots fired by Israeli forces during clashes in which Palestinian youths threw stones at soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet personnel who entered the camp, arrested two Palestinians and interrogated dozens of others. Abu Shalbak died of his wounds shortly after. At least one other Palestinian was injured in the clashes. After Abu Shalbak was wounded, armed Palestinians fired at the Israeli forces, lightly wounding a Border Police officer.
Fatally shot by soldiers staffing a military post at the intersection, after, according to the military, stabbing one of them and severely wounding him. Israel is holding his body.

Wounded by shots fired by soldiers and Border Police officers during about an hour-long fire exchange that broke out after the Israeli forces surrounded his house. The Israeli forces arrested Shalabi after he was wounded and announced his death a short time later. Bani Gharrah was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot by soldiers at a convenience store located near a meet-up site for Palestinian laborers, one of whom was wounded by the soldiers fire and died of his wounds shortly after. According to the military, Jaber was heading into Israel carrying an explosive device and was shot after he tried to pull out a gun when the soldiers called him out of the convenience store. Israel is holding his body.

Wounded by soldiers gunfire aimed at another Palestinian inside a convenience store nearby. According to the military, the soldiers arrived at the scene to arrest the Palestinian in the convenience store, who was allegedly planning to enter Israel with an explosive device, and shot him after he tried to pull out a gun. Hussein died of his wounds shortly after.

Wounded by Border Police officers gunfire while launching fireworks at the military tower at the checkpoint along with other minors. In video footage posted on social media, Hamdan is seen lighting a firework, and then being shot and falling to the ground. Died of his wounds shortly after. Israel held his body until 18 March 2024.

Shot in the side of the body, chest and thigh by Border Police officers, while he and four other Palestinians who had arrived at the Separation Fence near Route 436 by car began unloading Molotov cocktails. All four were wounded by the gunfire, including a minor who died of his wounds soon after. The Border Police officers fired from an ambush, at close range, and from several directions. Khalayfah's body was given to a Palestinian ambulance, and the remaining wounded were detained for several hours before being transferred to Palestinian ambulances at al-Jib Checkpoint (Giv'at Zeev).

Wounded by Border Police officers, while he and four other Palestinians who had arrived at the Separation Fence near Route 436 by car began unloading Molotov cocktails. All four were wounded by the gunfire. One of them was killed instantly. The Border Police officers fired from an ambush, at close range, and from several directions. Assaf and the remaining wounded were detained for several hours before being transferred to Palestinian ambulances at al-Jib Checkpoint (Giv'at Zeev). Assaf died of his wounds shortly after.

Wounded in the head by soldiers gunfire, while attempting to flee them into the Khalil a-Salman hospital compound in the city after he and other youths threw stones at military jeeps that were passing by on the way to Jenin R.C., where the Israeli forces arrested Palestinians. One of the youths, a Hamas military wing operative, was wounded and died of his wounds shortly after. Abu al-Heija died of his wounds shortly after as well.

Wounded by soldiers gunfire, while attempting to flee them into the Khalil a-Salman hospital compound in the city after he and other youths threw stones at military jeeps that were passing by on the way to Jenin R.C., where the Israeli forces arrested Palestinians. One of the youths was wounded and died of his wounds shortly after. Jalamneh, who was a Hamas military wing operative, died of his wounds shortly after as well.

Fatally shot by soldiers after, according to the military, arriving at a checkpoint on an electric bicycle, stabbing a soldier and a security guard who, according to the media, were lightly to moderately wounded. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot by soldiers while firing at homes in a Jewish settlement in Hebron City Center from inside the Karantina cemetery. Video footage posted on social media shows Nofal walking in the cemetery holding a rifle, and then being hit by the soldiers gunfire. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot by two Shin Bet men after firing at them and wounding them. According to media reports, one was lightly wounded and the other was severely wounded. Israel is holding his body. Hamran was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Fatally shot by one of three soldiers who came to his plot of land, while he was grazing his flock on it, about 100 meters away from his house. The soldiers, one of whom was masked, assaulted Bani Jaber, knocking him to the ground. When he picked up a stone to defend himself, one of them fatally shot him. The military claimed that the soldiers arrived after settlers reported an attack on a Jewish child in the area and that there were clashes at the scene, during which Palestinians threw stones. However, BTselems investigation shows there were no clashes at the scene.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft along with two other Islamic Jihad military wing operatives, while traveling in a car in the city together with a senior military wing operative. The senior operative was wounded and died the next day. According to the military and the Shin Bet, one of the operatives fatally shot an Israeli citizen in May 2023.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft along with two other Islamic Jihad military wing operatives, while traveling in a car in the city together with a senior military wing operative. The senior operative was wounded and died the next day. According to the military and the Shin Bet, he fatally shot an Israeli citizen in May 2023.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft along with two other Islamic Jihad military wing operatives, while traveling in a car in the city together with a senior military wing operative. The senior operative was wounded and died the next day. According to the military and the Shin Bet, one of the operatives fatally shot an Israeli citizen in May 2023.

Wounded by a missile fired from an aircraft along with three other Islamic Jihad military wing operatives, who were killed on the spot. According to the military and the Shin Bet, one of the operatives fatally shot an Israeli citizen in May 2023. Hawashin was a senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Shot in the head from a distance of about 100 meters by a Border Police officer, while hiding behind a car several minutes after throwing stones at armored military, Border Police and Israel Police vehicles, with other youths. The Israeli forces entered the neighborhoods of Kafr Aqab and Umm a-Sharayet and arrested Palestinians, and the youths threw stones at them as they were leaving. After the stone-throwing stopped, another Border Police jeep arrived and an officer stepped out of it, fired at Salhiyeh, and then at a youth who tried to help him, but missed.

Fatally shot by a soldier who claimed Zaitun looked suspicious. In a video recording posted on social media, Zaitun can be heard arguing with the soldier, who threatens him as he stands at a bus stop, obeying the soldiers orders to put his hands up, moments before he is shot at close range.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft together with another Islamic Jihad military wing operative, while participating in clashes, during which Palestinians fired and threw stones and explosive devices at soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet personnel who entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. According to the military, the two had thrown explosive devices. Two other operatives, one of them a minor and the other a Palestinian citizen of Israel, were wounded in the clashes and died shortly after.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft together with another Islamic Jihad military wing operative, a minor, while participating in clashes, during which Palestinians fired and threw stones and explosive devices at soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet personnel who entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. According to the military, the two had thrown explosive devices. Two other operatives, one of them a minor and the other a Palestinian citizen of Israel, were wounded in the clashes and died shortly after.

Wounded by Israeli forces fire, while participating in a fire exchange. During the fire exchange, Palestinians fired and threw stones and explosive devices at soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet personnel who entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. Another Islamic Jihad military wing operative, who was a Palestinian citizen of Israel, was also wounded in the fire exchange. Both were pronounced dead shortly after. Two other operatives, including a minor, were killed by a missile fired from an aircraft, after, according to the military, throwing explosive devices.

Wounded by shots fired by undercover Border Police officers, while throwing stones at them along with other youths after the officers entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. Died of his wounds shortly after. Armed men in the vicinity of the stone-throwers engaged in a fire exchange with the undercover officers.

Wounded by shots a Palestinian fired at the minibus he was traveling in. Died of his wounds shortly after. Six other soldiers were wounded by the gunfire. The shooter was killed by a missile fired from an aircraft during a fire exchange between him and the soldiers.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft during a fire exchange with soldier after firing at a minibus and wounding seven soldiers, one of whom died of his wounds soon after. Israel is holding Mansurs body.

Wounded by a missile fired from an aircraft while participating in clashes that broke out after soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet personnel entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. An officer with the Palestinian Authority security forces and an Islamic Jihad military wing operative were also killed in the missile strike. During the clashes, Palestinians fired and threw explosive devices at the Israeli forces. A Palestinian passerby was wounded by Israeli forces fire in the city of Jenin. He also died of his wounds shortly after. Al-Usta, who was an al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative, died of his wounds shortly after.

An officer with the Palestinian Authority security forces. Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft together with an Islamic Jihad military wing operative, while the two participated in clashes that broke out after soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet personnel entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. During the clashes, Palestinians fired and threw explosive devices at the Israeli forces. An al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative was wounded in the missile strike and died of his wounds shortly after, and another Palestinian passerby was wounded by Israeli forces fire in the city of Jenin. He also died of his wounds shortly after.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft together with an officer with the Palestinian Authority security forces, while the two participated in clashes that broke out after soldiers, Border Police officers and Shin Bet personnel entered the camp and arrested Palestinians. During the clashes, Palestinians fired and threw explosive devices at the Israeli forces. An al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative was wounded in the missile strike and died of his wounds shortly after. A Palestinian passerby was wounded by Israeli forces fire in the city of Jenin. He also died of his wounds shortly after. Bani Gharrah was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Wounded by Israeli forces gunfire while walking in the street while clashes were underway in various locations in the city of Jenin and in Jenin R.C.. The clashes broke out after soldiers, Shin Bet personnel and Border Police officers entered the city and arrested Palestinians.
