Shot while throwing an IED at military jeeps along with other youths, during clashes that developed after soldiers raided the Tulkarm neighborhood of Dhinnaba, which is adjacent to the refugee camp. During the clashes, armed Palestinians fired at the soldiers. Abd a-Dayem was a Hamas military wing operative.

Shot in the head by soldiers when warning residents that a military force had entered the camp. The military claimed he was armed. In the clashes that followed, which included stone-throwing and shooting by Palestinians at the soldiers, four Palestinians were injured and four others were arrested. During the raid, military bulldozers destroyed infrastructure in the camp.

Shot by soldiers in the back of the neck, chest, arm, abdomen and leg, when throwing an IED at them during clashes in which Palestinians also fired at the soldiers. The clashes developed after the soldiers entered the city and surrounded a home where armed Palestinians barricaded themselves. While in the town, the Israeli forces killed five more Palestinians. In a video posted on social media, Samudi is seen being shot twice while lying wounded on the ground.

Fatally shot during a fire exchange that developed with soldiers who surrounded the house where he was barricaded together with other Islamic Jihad military wing operatives, two of whom were also killed. The soldiers fired anti-tank missiles at the home. While in the town, the Israeli forces killed three more Palestinians.

Fatally shot by soldiers when participating in clashes that developed after the soldiers entered the city and surrounded a home where armed Palestinians barricaded themselves. During the clashes shots were fired and explosive devices were thrown at the soldiers. While in the town, the Israeli forces killed five more Palestinians.

Shot in the chest by soldiers after firing at them from the roof of his home during clashes that developed when the soldiers surrounded a nearby home where armed Palestinians barricaded themselves. While in the town, the Israeli forces killed five more Palestinians. Mari was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Shot in the head and all other parts of the body during a fire exchange that developed with soldiers who surrounded the house where he was barricaded together with other Islamic Jihad military wing operatives, two of whom were also killed. The soldiers fired anti-tank missiles at the home. While in the town, the Israeli forces killed three more Palestinians.

Shot in the head, chest and thigh during a fire exchange that developed with soldiers who surrounded the house where he was barricaded together with other Islamic Jihad military wing operatives, two of whom were also killed. The soldiers fired anti-tank missiles at the home. While in the town, the Israeli forces killed three more Palestinians.

Shot in the head, thigh and groin by soldiers and Border Police officers when firing at them during a fire exchange that developed after the Israeli forces surrounded a house and killed two senior Islamic Jihad military wing operatives. During the clashes, Palestinians also threw IEDs and fired at the forces.

Killed along with another senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative during a fire exchange with soldiers who surrounded the house where they were barricaded. The soldiers also fired shoulder-mounted missiles at the house and a military bulldozer destroyed parts of it. Another Palestinian was killed when firing at the forces in clashes that developed following the siege on the house. During these clashes, Palestinians threw IEDs at the Israeli forces. Israel is holding his body.

Killed along with another senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative during a fire exchange with soldiers who surrounded the house where they were barricaded. The soldiers also fired shoulder-mounted missiles at the house and a military bulldozer destroyed parts of it. Another Palestinian was killed when firing at the forces in clashes that developed following the siege on the house. During these clashes, Palestinians threw IEDs at the Israeli forces. Israel is holding his body.

Wounded in the abdomen by shots fired by soldiers who raided a car wash, fired at an employee, severely wounding him as well. According to media reports, the soldiers were searching for a Palestinian driving a suspected stolen vehicle who hit a soldier at the Rantis checkpoint. Hushiyeh was on his way home when he noticed the soldiers and started running to get away from them, near a site where Palestinians were throwing stones at them. The soldiers delayed Hushiyehs evacuation for about 20 minutes. Later, the soldiers fired at another Palestinian, an American citizen, who was driving past a military jeep, severely wounding him.

Shot by soldiers and Border Police officers while throwing stones at them along with other youths, after the forces entered the town. Two more Palestinians were wounded by the Israeli forces fire. Died of his wounds shortly after.

A man with a psychosocial disability. Fatally shot by the security guards of the Migdal Oz settlement, near the western entrance to the town. According to media reports, Balalu was spotted on security cameras as he approached the settlement. The security guards then approached him, and, according to the military, fired at him as he ran towards them with a knife drawn. Israel is holding his body.

Shot by soldiers after throwing stones at them along with other minors, and then escaping. The soldiers entered the city to confiscate security cameras on the main street, where an Israeli citizen was attacked earlier, and, according to media reports, died due to a cardiac event. Samha died of his wounds shortly after.

Fatally shot by ssoldiers and police officers (from the Gidonim unit) along with an Islamic Jihad military wing operative, who was also killed, in a fire exchange that developed between them and the officers, as they rode in a car through the city center. Video footage released by the army shows the car crashing into shops on the street. Zeid was an Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative. Israel is holding their bodies.

Fatally shot by soldiers and police officers (from the Gidonim unit) along with an al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative, who was also killed, in a fire exchange that developed between them and the officers, as they rode in a car through the city center. Video footage released by the army shows the car crashing into shops on the street. Abu Hamed was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding their bodies.

Shot by Palestinians while inside his car shortly after arriving in the city, apparently for shopping. Muchtar was evacuated by a Palestinian ambulance team to the hospital in the city and from there by Israeli forces to a checkpoint, where, according to media reports, he was pronounced dead. His car was set on fire after he was evacuated.

Killed when in the explosion of an explosive device hidden by Palestinians on a street in the camp, when he arrived at the scene and advanced on foot with other soldiers towards a military vehicle that sustained damage earlier when another explosive device detonated. Sixteen other soldiers were wounded in the two explosions. According to media reports, one sustained severe injuries and the others sustained light to moderate injuries.
Wounded by a missile fired from an aircraft at the home he was in with other Palestinians, one of whom was killed and five of whom were wounded. Abdallah was an Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft at the home he was in with other Palestinians, six of whom were wounded. One died of his wounds roughly five days later. Jaber was a senior Hamas military wing operative.

Killed when the military vehicle he was driving mounted an explosive device about four hours after Israeli forces raided the camp. According to the military, an officer was seriously injured in the explosion. During the raid, which continued the next day, four Palestinians were killed.

Killed when a missile fired from an aircraft hit the tin roof of her kitchen, while she was sitting in the living room with her sister-in-law, who was wounded. The missile was fired while armed Palestinians were shooting at Israeli forces as they retreated after a raid of nearby Nur Shams Refugee Camp, where they destroyed infrastructure. A soldier was killed by an IED explosion at the beginning of the raid. During their retreat, the Israeli forces fatally shot a minor who was standing on a street in the city.

Shot by Israeli armed forces on the street. Security camera footage shows Sarhan, masked, attempting to find cover and then being shot and falling. The forces destroyed infrastructure in nearby Nur Shams Refugee Camp earlier, where a soldier was killed by and IED at the start of the raid. Clashes developed between them and Palestinians, during which armed Palestinians fired at the forces. During the raid, in nearby Tulkarm Refugee Camp, a woman was killed and another was injured by a missile that was fired from an aircraft and landed on their roof.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft along with three other Palestinians, while trying to lay down an explosive device on a street at the center of the camp. Shhadeh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. During the raid, which lasted about two days, a soldier was killed by an explosive device.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft along with three other Palestinians, while trying to lay down an explosive device on a street at the center of the camp. Shafi was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. During the raid, which lasted about two days, a soldier was killed by an explosive device.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft along with three other Palestinians, while trying to lay down an explosive device on a street at the center of the camp. Kanuh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. During the raid, which lasted about two days, a soldier was killed by an explosive device.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft along with three other Palestinians, while trying to lay down an explosive device on a street at the center of the camp. Ibrahim was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. During the raid, which lasted about two days, a soldier was killed by an explosive device.

Shot in the head and torso by undercover Border Police officers who arrived in four civilian jeeps bearing Palestinian license plates at the Jenin industrial zone, along with soldiers. The jeeps drove against traffic until they reached a car wash, where the first jeep hit Amer, and then all the jeeps stopped. Amer, who had been standing and talking to others at the scene, fell to the ground, and then two members of the force got out of the jeep that hit him and announced in Arabic that they were members of a special unit. Immediately after that, one of them shot Amer at least twice, and then the third shot hit his head. The two members of the armed forces then got back inside the jeep and all the jeeps drove off. 'Amer was a senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft while shooting, along with four other armed men, at Israeli soldiers who entered the area of al-Awdah Square, on the west side of the camp. Three of the armed men were killed on site and one died of his wounds about two days later. During the raid on the city and the refugee camp, three more Palestinians were killed in the city and one was wounded. Ashqar died of his wounds on 15 October 2024. He was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft while shooting, along with four other armed men, at Israeli soldiers who entered the area of al-Awdah Square, on the west side of the camp. Three of the armed men were killed on site and one died of his wounds about two days later. During the raid on the city and the refugee camp, three more Palestinians were killed in the city and one was wounded. Ashqar died of his wounds on 15 October 2024. He was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft while shooting, along with four other armed men, at Israeli soldiers who entered the area of al-Awdah Square, on the west side of the camp. Three of the armed men were killed on site and one died of his wounds about two days later. During the raid on the city and the refugee camp, three more Palestinians were killed in the city and one was wounded. Ashqar died of his wounds on 15 October 2024. He was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Wounded by a missile fired from an aircraft while shooting, along with four other armed men who were killed instantly, at Israeli soldiers who entered the area of al-Awdah Square, on the west side of the camp. During the raid on the city and the refugee camp, three more Palestinians were killed in the city and one was wounded. Ashqar died of his wounds on 15 October 2024. Abu al-Heija was a Hamas military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft while shooting, along with four other armed men, at Israeli soldiers who entered the area of al-Awdah Square, on the west side of the camp. Three of the armed men were killed on site and one died of his wounds about two days later. During the raid on the city and the refugee camp, three more Palestinians were killed in the city and one was wounded. Ashqar died of his wounds on 15 October 2024. Al-Aridi was a Hamas military wing operative.

Fatally shot while with his son, who was wounded, in their home, which is under construction. The soldiers who fired were surrounding a house in a nearby neighborhood, where they killed two other Palestinians, during a military and Shin Bet raid on the camp. Jabarins son died of his wounds about three months later. During the raid that day, the soldiers killed five more Palestinians in the camp.

Wounded while with his father, who was fatally shot, in their home, which is under construction. The soldiers who fired were surrounding a house in a nearby neighborhood, where they killed two other Palestinians, during a military and Shin Bet raid on the camp. During the raid that day, the soldiers killed five more Palestinians in the camp.

Killed along with his brother during a fire exchange that developed between the two and soldiers who were surrounding their house and fired anti-tank missiles at it. Hashash was a Hamas military wing operative. During the raid that day, soldiers killed six more Palestinians and wounded another, who died of his wounds about three months later.

Killed along with his brother during a fire exchange that developed between the two and soldiers who were surrounding their house and fired anti-tank missiles at it. Hashash was a Hamas military wing operative. During the raid that day, soldiers killed six more Palestinians and wounded another, who died of his wounds about three months later.

Hit in the chest and thigh by soldiers gunfire while driving with two friends, who were wounded and arrested near Route 443. Suliman was apparently removed from the car by soldiers and placed naked on the ground near Maccabim checkpoint. A Palestinian ambulance team that was given permission to evacuate him only 45 minutes after arriving at the scene found him dead. The media reported that, according to the military, the cars passengers threw Molotov cocktails near the village.

Fatally stabbed by a Palestinian who broke into his home while he was sleeping. The two got into an argument, and the Palestinian stabbed Avni dozens of times all over his body. He then tried to set fire to the apartment, stole several items and fled.
Shot in the abdomen by members of a civilian emergency response team while throwing stones with other minors at Route 465 near the village. His body was found by local residents.

Shot while throwing stones along with other minors at military jeeps passing through the western entrance to the village after having arrested Palestinians in a nearby village. Two of the jeeps stopped when an armed Palestinian located far from the minors fired at them and fled. The soldiers fired at the group of minors. Another teen was wounded and died of his wounds shortly after, and, according to the media, five other teens were wounded.

Shot while throwing stones along with other minors at military jeeps passing through the western entrance to the village after having arrested Palestinians in a nearby village. Two of the jeeps stopped when an armed Palestinian located far from the minors fired at them and fled. The soldiers fired at the group of minors. Another teen was wounded and died of his wounds on 23 July 2024, and, according to the media, five other teens were wounded.

Shot in the abdomen during clashes that developed after soldiers entered the village when a wedding luncheon was taking place. During the clashes, Palestinians threw stones and Molotov cocktails at the soldiers. A video posted on social media shows Muzahem fleeing from the road toward nearby homes with a group of young men. A Palestinian was arrested during the clashes.

Seriously wounded when hit by a car driven by a Palestinian resident of East Jerusalem while waiting at a bus stop at the Nir Zvi intersection on Route 44. The vehicle ran over soldiers at two bust stops on both sides of the road. Three other soldiers were injured by the vehicle, one of them seriously. The driver was fatally shot by Border Police officers who stopped at the scene.

Fatally shot by Border Police officer after running over soldiers in two bus stops on both sides of Route 44, at the Nir Zvi junction. Four soldiers were injured by the car, two of them seriously. One died of his wounds on 24 July 2024. Israel is holding Shihabs body.

Shot by soldiers who raided the city to confiscate funds from money changers, after, allegedly, stabbing and lightly wounding one of them before fleeing into a construction site. His body was handed over to the Palestinian Red Crescent about two hours after he was shot.

Shot in the head by soldiers at a distance of about 200 meters from his home in clashes during which Palestinians threw stones and fired firecrackers at them. The military claimed they threw stones. Died of his wounds shortly after.
Shot by soldiers while trying to flee after throwing stones at military jeeps that were retreating from the village after soldiers raided several homes.

Shot in the thigh by soldiers while complying with their orders to back away after an argument with them. The soldiers raided homes in the town and youths threw stones at them about 300 meters from Shalaldas house. Shalaldah, who was on his way to dawn prayer at the mosque, came across the soldiers, who were blocking the path of an ambulance that was taking a woman in labor to a hospital, and demanded they let it pass. The soldiers ordered him to back away and when he complied, they shot him. Died of his wounds shortly after.

Wounded by shots fired by soldiers who came to arrest him and two other Palestinians, one of whom was also wounded. The soldiers tied Raddad to the hood of a military jeep that drove away. That day, Israeli forces killed six more Palestinians in the camp. Raddad died in an Israeli hospital in IPS custody. He was a Hamas military wing operative.

Wounded in the upper body by Israeli armed forces fire while taking part in a fire exchange during clashes that developed following a military, Border Police and Shin Bet raid of the camp. During the raid, which began the night before, five other Palestinians were killed by missile fired from an aircraft during an assassination, including three armed men and a mother and daughter who were next to them on the street. Abdu was an al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft along with two other armed men, a woman and her daughter, during a raid by military, Border Police and Shin Bet personnel. The three men were the target of a military assassination. During the raid, a fire exchange between Israeli forces and Palestinian operatives took place elsewhere in the camp. One operative was killed by Israeli forces gunfire. A video posted on social media shows a military bulldozer taking the bodies of four of the dead away. Nafea was a senior Hamas military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft along with two other armed men, a woman and her daughter, during a raid by military, Border Police and Shin Bet personnel. The three men were the target of a military assassination. During the raid, a fire exchange between Israeli forces and Palestinian operatives took place elsewhere in the camp. One operative was killed by Israeli forces gunfire. A video posted on social media shows a military bulldozer taking the bodies of four of the dead away. Abu Abdu was a senior al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft along with two other armed men, a woman and her daughter, during a raid by military, Border Police and Shin Bet personnel. The three men were the target of a military assassination. During the raid, a fire exchange between Israeli forces and Palestinian operatives took place elsewhere in the camp. One operative was killed by Israeli forces gunfire. A video posted on social media shows a military bulldozer taking the bodies of four of the dead away. Radwan was a senior al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft along with her mother and three armed Palestinians, who were near them on the street, during a raid by military, Border Police and Shin Bet personnel. The three men were the target of a military assassination. During the raid, a fire exchange between Israeli forces and Palestinian operatives took place elsewhere in the camp. One operative was killed by Israeli forces gunfire. A video posted on social media shows a military bulldozer taking the bodies of four of the dead away. Israel is holding her body.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft along with her daughter and three armed Palestinians, who were near them on the street, during a raid by military, Border Police and Shin Bet personnel. The three men were the target of a military assassination. Abeid was killed minutes after taking a photo holding one of the armed mens firearms. During the raid, a fire exchange between Israeli forces and Palestinian operatives took place elsewhere in the camp. One operative was killed by Israeli forces gunfire. A video posted on social media shows a military bulldozer taking the bodies of four of the dead away.

Wounded by shots fired from soldiers from inside an apartment they took over as part of a raid of the camp for purposes of a punitive house demolition, while throwing stones at soldiers in the street from a rooftop with another Palestinian. Died of his wounds shortly after.

Member of the Palestinian Authority security forces. Shot in the head, chest, knee and leg by soldiers, some in civilian clothing and some in uniforms. According to the military, Sarhan was killed "in an altercation," but B'Tselem's investigation indicates he advanced toward the soldiers, who arrived in a civilian vehicle with a Palestinian license plate, to check their IDs as part of his duty as a customs officer. One of the soldiers fired two shots at him, and after Sarhan fell to the ground, another soldier shot him again. The soldiers also fired at other customs officers who tried to evacuate him, injuring two of them, and prevented an ambulance crew from approaching him. While in Tubas, the soldiers arrested two Palestinians and one soldier was lightly injured.

Volunteer paramedic. Struck in the head by a missile fired from an aircraft in the al-Jamasin neighborhood during a military raid on the camp. Two other paramedics who were with him tried to evacuate him, but the soldiers fired at them and they had to flee. They returned later and, with the help of residents, took Saqer to an ambulance that was waiting about 250 meters away. An additional 28 Palestinians were injured by the missile or by soldier gunfire in clashes that developed at various locations during the raid, and two of them died of their wounds shortly after.

Wounded in a fire exchange with soldiers who entered the camp. During the raid, 28 more Palestinians were injured by a missile or by soldier gunfire in clashes that developed at various locations in the camp.Two of the missile strike victims, including a volunteer paramedic, died of their wounds a short while later.Hashash was an al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative.

Wounded on the street by a missile fired from an aircraft during a raid of the camp. The military claims the missile was fired at armed operatives. A volunteer paramedic was also killed by the missile strike, and 27 Palestinians were injured by the missile or by soldier gunfire in clashes that developed at various locations during the raid. One of them also died of his wounds shortly after. Mashah was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.
Shot in the head by soldiers, according to the military, after trying to stab them at the Beit Einun junction. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot by soldiers while fleeing them. Video footage shows Sadeq throwing stones along with several other Palestinians at a convoy of military vehicles passing on the street below them. One of the vehicles at the end of the convoy stops, and two soldiers get out and run towards the stone throwers. At this point, the Palestinians begin fleeing the soldiers, who fatally shoot Sadeq.
Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with four other armed Palestinians, while they were riding in a car near the town. Sabbag was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.
Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with four other armed Palestinians, while they were riding in a car near the town. Bleidi was a Hamas military wing operative.
Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with four other armed Palestinians, while they were riding in a car near the town. Khalil was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.
Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with four other armed Palestinians, while they were riding in a car near the town. Abu Haniyeh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.
Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with four other armed Palestinians, while they were riding in a car near the town. Mahajnah was a Hamas military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with three other armed Palestinians while in an agricultural area between the town of Attil and the village of Iktaba, northwest of the city of Tulkarm. The military claims they fired at soldiers who were in the area. Masharqah was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with three other armed Palestinians while in an agricultural area between the town of Attil and the village of Iktaba, northwest of the city of Tulkarm. The military claims they fired at soldiers who were in the area. Shaf'a was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with three other armed Palestinians while in an agricultural area between the town of Attil and the village of Iktaba, northwest of the city of Tulkarm. The military claims they fired at soldiers who were in the area. Karawi was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with three other armed Palestinians while in an agricultural area between the town of Attil and the village of Iktaba, northwest of the city of Tulkarm. The military claims they fired at soldiers who were in the area. Hamedi was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Suffered critical wounds when a Palestinian stabbed him. Died of his wounds at the hospital. A police officer who was at the scene immediately shot the assailant, critically wounding him. He died of his wounds at the hospital. Earlier, the same Palestinian stabbed three other Israeli civilians, one of whom died of her wounds a short time later.

Sustained critical injuries when a Palestinian stabbed her. Died of her wounds shortly after. The same Palestinian stabbed three other Israeli civilians, one of whom died of his at the hospital. Her husband was among the injured. A police officer who was at the scene shot the assailant, critically wounding him. He died of his wounds at the hospital.

Shot and critically wounded by an Israeli police officer after stabbing and wounding four Israeli civilians, two of whom sustained critical injuries and died shortly after. The other two sustained severe and moderate injuries. Died of his wounds at the hospital. Israel is holding his body.

Wounded in the back by shots fired by Israeli armed forces that raided the city and Jenin R.C., while on his way home. In the clashes that developed in the city and the camp during the raid, Palestinians threw stones and explosive devices at the Israeli forces and fired at them. Another Palestinian was injured in the city and died of his wounds on 11 August 2024.

Wounded by shots fired by Israeli armed forces that raided the city and Jenin R.C., while on his way home In the clashes that developed in the city and the camp during the raid, Palestinians threw stones and explosive devices at the Israeli forces and fired at them. Another Palestinian was injured in the city and died of his wounds on 16 September 2024.

Fatally shot near his home by soldiers and undercover Border Police officers who entered the village, surrounded a nearby house and killed a Palestinian who was in it in a fire exchange. Another Palestinian was killed by the Israeli forces fire in clashes that broke out in the town following their entry, and seven others were injured. In the nearby city of Tubas, a Palestinian was killed in clashes that developed near the Turkish Hospital in the city, as the forces withdrew from the nearby town of Aqqabah.

Shot in the neck by soldiers and undercover Border Police officers when participating in clashes in which Palestinians threw stones and explosive devices at the Israeli forces that entered the town and fired at them. The forces surrounded a house where they killed another Palestinian during a fire exchange. Another Palestinian was killed and seven were injured by the Israeli forces fire in the town. During their retreat from the town, the Israeli forces fatally shot a Palestinian minor in the nearby city of Tubas. Yasin was a Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Fatally shot by soldiers and Border Police officers after getting off a bus that was stopped for a security check at the Tunnel Checkpoint, along with all other passengers. The police claimed he was shot after stabbing a police officer causing minor injuries. Israel is holding his body.

Killed in a fire exchange with undercover Border Police officers who surrounded his house with soldiers in order to arrest him. The military claims he was killed while trying to escape through the window. The forces killed two more Palestinians while in the town. During their retreat, they killed a Palestinian minor in the city of Tubas. Ghanam was a Hamas military wing operative.

Severely injured by Israeli armed forces gunfire while trying to flee a house surrounded by the Israeli forces, along with four other Palestinians, two of whom were also severely wounded and two of whom were killed. The forces prevented their evacuation in a Palestinian ambulance and arrested him and the other two wounded men. The military claims they fired at the Israeli forces. Abu Qutnah was an al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed by Israeli armed forces gunfire along with another Palestinian, as the two tried to flee a house surrounded by the Israeli forces, along with three other Palestinians, who were severely wounded in the shooting. The forces prevented their evacuation in a Palestinian ambulance and arrested the three wounded men, one of whom died of his wounds on 11 August 2024. The military claims they fired at the Israeli forces. Hussein was a senior al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed by Israeli armed forces gunfire along with another Palestinian, as the two tried to flee a house surrounded by the Israeli forces, along with three other Palestinians, who were severely wounded in the shooting. The forces prevented their evacuation in a Palestinian ambulance and arrested the three wounded men, one of whom died of his wounds on 11 August 2024. The military claims they fired at the Israeli forces. Abu Qutnah was an al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed by missiles fired from an aircraft while on the street with other Palestinians, four of whom were instantly killed. Another was injured and died of wounds the next day. All six fired or threw IEDs. Video footage released by the military shows two of the dead on a scooter and two injured armed men near them. Clashes broke out in the camp, during which Palestinians threw IEDs and fired at the Israeli forces.

Killed by missiles fired from an aircraft while on the street with other Palestinians, four of whom, one a minor, were instantly killed. Another was injured and died of his wounds the next day. All six fired or threw IEDs. Video footage released by the military shows two of the dead on a scooter and two injured armed men near them. Clashes broke out in the camp, during which Palestinians threw IEDs and fired at the Israeli forces. A-S'adi was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed by missiles fired from an aircraft while on the street with other Palestinians, four of whom, one a minor, were instantly killed. Another was injured and died of his wounds the next day. All six fired or threw IEDs. Video footage released by the military shows two of the dead on a scooter and two injured armed men near them. Clashes broke out in the camp, during which Palestinians threw IEDs and fired at the Israeli forces. Zakarneh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed by missiles fired from an aircraft while on the street with other Palestinians, including his brother. Four of them, one a minor, were instantly killed and another was injured and died of his wounds the next day. All six fired or threw IEDs. Video footage released by the military shows two of the dead on a scooter and two injured armed men near them. Clashes broke out in the camp, during which Palestinians threw IEDs and fired at the Israeli forces. Abu 'Ubeid was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed by missiles fired from an aircraft while on the street with other Palestinians, including his brother. Four of them, one a minor, were instantly killed and another was injured and died of his wounds the next day. All six fired or threw IEDs. Video footage released by the military shows two of the dead on a scooter and two injured armed men near them. Clashes broke out in the camp, during which Palestinians threw IEDs and fired at the Israeli forces. Abu 'Ubeid was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Injured by missiles fired from an aircraft while on the street with other Palestinians, four of whom, one a minor, were instantly killed, and another was injured and died of his wounds the next day. All six fired or threw IEDs. Video footage released by the military shows two of the dead on a scooter and two injured armed men near them. Clashes broke out in the camp, during which Palestinians threw IEDs and fired at the Israeli forces. Abu Hijab was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Fatally shot by soldiers in ambush. The military claimed he was armed and had attempted to fire at the settlement of Beka'ot. Daraghmeh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Shot in the abdomen and shoulder by soldiers and undercover Border Police officers near the Turkish Hospital in the city, while waiting, along with other locals, in the hospitals square, for the bodies of three Palestinians killed by Israeli forces in the nearby town of Aqqabah. Clashes broke out in the area between residents and retreating Israeli forces.

Critically wounded by shots fired from a passing Palestinian car, while driving. Deutsch lost control of his vehicle following impact and skidded to the side of the road. The Palestinians fired at another vehicle nearby, hitting a Palestinian citizen of Israel who was lightly wounded. Deutsch died of his wounds shortly after.

Fatally shot by soldiers at the end of a chase after shooting and wounding an Israeli citizen who entered Qalqiliyah to have his car fixed. According to media reports, he also killed two Palestinians who were at the site. Dawood was a Hamas military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.
