The military claimed the soldiers believed an armed Palestinian was in the home and called for the occupants to vacate it over loudspeakers prior to firing. The family say they did not hear such a call.

Wounded by undercover Border Police gunfire together with two other Palestinians, after, according to the police, they threw an explosive device at the officers near a checkpoint. Taken to a hospital in Ramallah, where he died of his wounds shortly after.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with Ihab Eteiwi, a Hamas military wing operative, in a targeted killing aimed at Eteiwi, while the two were traveling in a car at the entrance to the camp, during Operation Iron Wall. Four passersby were injured by the missile. Zamel was a Hamas military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with another Palestinian inside a car at the entrance to the camp in a targeted killing aimed at him during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Four passersby were injured by the missile. E'teiwi was a Hamas military wing operative.

Shot by soldiers in the chest, pelvis, arm and lower limbs when he stepped out to look for his brother, after hearing gunfire on a nearby street. Naji fell near the house, but family members were unable to help him because the shooting continued. The soldiers demanded his cousin turn himself in, and only after he did so was Naji evacuated in a military ambulance but died of his wounds. His body was transferred to the family via the Red Crescent. Israeli soldiers killed a Palestinian minor in another neighborhood of Tulkarm on the same day.

Wounded in the back by soldiers gunfire while standing near his front entrance. Rajab was taken to the hospital in an ambulance, while the soldiers detained his father and other neighbors who came to help him, arresting three of them. He underwent surgery at the hospital, but succumbed to his wounds 10 days later. The military initially claimed that 10-year-old Rajab was messing with the ground in a suspicious way. Israeli soldiers killed another Palestinian in another neighborhood of Tulkarm on the same day.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft after he threw an explosive device from the roof of a building near Cinema Square at Israeli forces who raided the camp as part of Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. His body was found the next day by a Red Crescent team.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with nine other Palestinians, including a pair of siblings and a minor, while sitting in a yard belonging to one of them, during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian was wounded in the attack. Khatib was a Hamas military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with nine other Palestinians, including a pair of siblings and a minor, while sitting in a yard belonging to one of them, during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian was wounded in the attack. Bani Matar was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with nine other Palestinians, including a pair of siblings and a minor, while sitting in a yard belonging to one of them, during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian was wounded in the attack. Bani Odeh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with nine other Palestinians, including his brother and a minor, while sitting in a yard belonging to one of them, during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian was wounded in the attack. Bani Odeh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with nine other Palestinians, including his brother and a minor, during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank, while sitting in a yard belonging to one of them. Another Palestinian was wounded in the attack. Bani Odeh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with nine other Palestinians, including a pair of siblings and a minor, while sitting in a yard belonging to one of them, during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian was wounded in the attack. Bani 'Odeh was a Hamas military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with nine other Palestinians, including a pair of siblings and a minor, while sitting in a yard belonging to one of them, during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian was wounded in the attack. Bsharat was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with nine other Palestinians, including a pair of siblings and a minor, while sitting in a yard belonging to one of them, during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian was wounded in the attack. Bani Matar was a Hamas military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with nine other Palestinians, including a pair of siblings and a minor, while sitting in a yard belonging to one of them, during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian was wounded in the attack. Bsharat was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft with nine other Palestinians, including a pair of siblings, while sitting in a yard belonging to one of them, during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian was wounded in the attack. Bani Matar was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Wounded by shots fired by armed Palestinians during a fire exchange after entering a home in the camp with other soldiers, six of whom were also injured, as part of Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Later that day, soldiers and Shin Bet personnel killed two Palestinians in the camp who they said were the armed men who shot Hazi. Died of his wounds shortly after. One of the other soldiers was severely injured and three were moderately injured.

Member of the Palestinian Authority security forces. Fatally shot by soldiers and Special Police Unit officers who came to arrest him while he was on the street with his wife and minor children. The Israeli police claimed al-Aklik had a gun and tried to escape. Al-Aklik was a senior al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot along with another Palestinian during a fire exchange with soldiers in a targeted killing aimed at both them. The military and the Shin Bet claimed the two fatally shot a soldier and wounded six others earlier that day. The soldiers had entered a house in the camp. al-Hassan was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot along with another Palestinian during a fire exchange with soldiers in a targeted killing aimed at both of them. The military and the Shin Bet claimed the two fatally shot a soldier and wounded six others earlier that day. The soldiers had entered a house in the camp as part of Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Abu Hassan was a Hamas military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed along with his father when a missile fired from an aircraft struck the car in which they were traveling during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. A father and his 15-year-old son, who were sitting in their car near their grocery store, were also injured by the missile. The son died of his wounds about two weeks later. The military claimed Kmeil and the Palestinian traveling with him were on their way to carry out a terrorist attack. Kmeil was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Killed along with his father when a missile fired from an aircraft struck the car in which they were traveling during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. A father and his 15-year-old son, who were sitting in their car near their grocery store, were also injured by the missile. The son died of his wounds about two weeks later. The military claimed Zakarnah and his friend were on their way to carry out a terrorist attack. Zakarnah was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Injured along with his father when a missile fired from an aircraft struck a car that passed by them while they were sitting in their car near their grocery store during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. The two Palestinians who were traveling in the car at which the missile was aimed were killed. Sabaanah was taken to a hospital, where he was hospitalized for about two weeks before succumbing to his wounds.

Killed along with his cousin by a missile fired from an aircraft while the two were riding a motorcycle, a few hours after the army fired a missile at a nearby location, hitting three of their relatives, including a child who was killed, during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Israeli armed forces were present in the city and the camp at the time, but not in the vicinity of the incident. A-Sadi was a Hamas military wing operative.

Killed by a missile fired from an aircraft that hit a group of people standing near his home. Two of his relatives were injured. Several hours later, the army fired another missile at a nearby location, killing two of his relatives while they were riding a motorcycle. The attack was carried out as part of Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Israeli armed forces were present in the city and the camp at the time, but not in the vicinity of the incident.

Killed along with his cousin, a Hamas military wing operative, by a missile fired from an aircraft while the two were riding a motorcycle, a few hours after the army fired a missile at a nearby location, hitting three of their relatives, including a child who was killed, during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Israeli armed forces were present in the city and the camp at the time, but not in the vicinity of the incident.

Injured by Israeli forces gunfire near his home when he went out to bring groceries for his family during the invasion of Israeli forces as part of Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Madi was taken to a hospital in Tulkarm where he died of his wounds shortly after.

Shot by Israeli forces who raided the camp during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank, while on his way to collect essential items from his home, which he and his family had to flee at the beginning of the operation. Lahluh was taken to a hospital in Jenin, deceased on arrival. The army claimed he was shot after being identified as a suspect spying on the forces.

A Palestinian Authority customs officer. Shot in the abdomen by soldiers from a distance of about 250 meters during clashes that developed in the camp, in which two minors were injured. Ahdush was standing at a friends doorway with three friends, having arrived to invite them to his engagement announcement party due to take place that day. He was taken by car to al-Ahli Hospital in Hebron, where he died of his wounds shortly after.

Fatally shot along with another soldier by a Palestinian who ambushed them at the entrance to a military post and fired at them when they came out and headed toward a nearby checkpoint, as well as at soldiers inside the post. A fire exchange ensued, in which eight more soldiers were wounded, two of them severely, and the Palestinian shooter was ultimately killed by a grenade thrown at him.

Fatally shot along with another soldier by a Palestinian who ambushed them at the entrance to a military post and fired at them when they came out and headed toward a nearby checkpoint, as well as at soldiers inside the post. A fire exchange ensued, in which eight more soldiers were wounded, two of them severely, and the Palestinian shooter was ultimately killed by a grenade thrown at him.

Killed by a fragmentation grenade thrown at him by soldiers after ambushing a military post, fatally shooting two soldiers exiting it and firing at soldiers in the post and a nearby checkpoint. In the fire exchange that ensued, eight more soldiers were wounded, two of them severely. Israel is holding his body.

Shot in the back by Israeli forces while trying to leave the camp in a car with her husband and brother-in-law following the army invasion during the Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Shalabi was eight months pregnant. The Israeli forces fired at their car, severely wounding her husband, and when she and her brother-in-law got out of the car, they detained the brother-in-law and shortly afterwards shot her as she stood next to the car, and took off. The military reportedly claimed she was shot because she was shot because she "looked suspiciously at the ground." Due to military activity in the area, Palestinian medical teams were only able to evacuate her after several hours, when it was no longer possible to save her or the fetus.

Killed with her father when Israeli forces detonated an explosive device they placed next to her front door during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. The military claims intelligence information indicated an armed operative was in the house, and the forces notified the residents before detonating the bomb on a loudspeaker. However, B'Tselem's investigation indicates the occupants never heard a call. After blowing up the door, the soldiers used a Palestinian as a human shield to approach the house and tell all the men to step out. They then detained al-Ashqar's uncle, who was placed in administrative detention. The forces remained in the house for about 15 minutes but did not provide any medical attention to al-Ashqar or her father.

Fatally shot by Israeli forces during a fire exchange that developed between them and armed Palestinians after the forces raided the camp during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. His body was found several hours later in an alley and taken to the hospital. Al-Akhras was a Hamas military wing operative.

Wounded in the chest by soldiers' fire. The soldiers then surrounded him and stood around him for about 15 minutes without providing him with medical attention. After they left, al-Froukh was taken to a hospital in Hebron, where he was pronounced dead. The military claims a "violent disturbance" developed at the scene, but video footage of the incident shows al-Froukh walking alone, with no one around him, throwing a single stone from a distance at the soldiers, then being shot and falling. During the army raid on the town, to confiscate mechanical equipment from a nearby factory, soldiers injured at least two more Palestinians, including a girl who lost her eyesight.

Fatally shot along with a Palestinian minor in a fire exchange between them and Israeli soldiers who raided the camp during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian was killed earlier in a fire exchange. According to the military, a soldier was moderately injured. Abu 'Abed was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot in a fire exchange with Israeli soldiers who raided the camp during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. After he was killed, two other Palestinians, including a minor, were fatally shot during the same fire exchange. According to the military, a soldier was moderately injured. Photos posted on social media showed Amer's body in the bucket of a military bulldozer, covered. Amer was a Hamas military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot along with a Palestinian minor in a fire exchange between them and Israeli soldiers who raided the camp during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian was killed earlier in a fire exchange. According to the military, a soldier was moderately injured. Masharqah was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot by soldiers near the Samaria Brigade headquarters after arriving there in a car. The military claimed soldiers shot him when he advanced towards them suspiciously. In photos posted on social media, Jabali's body is seen next to the car. Israel is holding his body.

Shot by soldiers while throwing stones at military jeeps standing by the 'Azmut roundabout, in the eastern section of the camp. In clashes that broke out between the soldiers and Palestinians, young men threw stones at the soldiers and one of them hurled an IED. Taken to hospital, where he was pronounced dead.

Fatally shot along with another Palestinian in a fire exchange with Israeli soldiers and undercover Border Police officers during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian who was with them was critically injured and detained by the forces. His family does not know if he is still alive. Khalil was an al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot along with another Palestinian in a fire exchange with Israeli soldiers and undercover Border Police officers during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian who was with them was critically injured and detained by the forces. His family does not know if he is still alive. Tayeh was a senior al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigade operative. Israel is holding his body.

Injured when a military jeep driving against traffic collided with the car in which he was traveling with his wife near the northern entrance to the camp. His wife, who was sitting next to him, was also injured. Awwad was taken to al-Israa Hospital in Tulkarm, where he died of his wounds several hours later.

He was injured by soldier gunfire when he and his younger brother left their grandfather's house and went toward their uncle's house. Soldiers who approached him did not provide him with medical treatment, delayed his evacuation for a short time, and fired at a relative who tried to evacuate him. The soldiers then left the scene. Al-Haymuni was taken to a hospital in a relative's car, where doctors tried unsuccessfully to perform CPR on him and had to pronounce him dead.

Injured in the back by soldiers gunfire while on her way from her home to a neighbors house during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. The soldiers continued to fire at the location as family members tried to evacuate her. The evacuation succeeded only several minutes after the shooting stopped, and Amuri was pronounced dead upon arrival at the hospital.

Shot in the chest by Border Police officers in clashes that developed after forces entered the city, raided homes, and deployed in the western cemetery. During the clashes, in which Palestinians threw stones at the forces, seven Palestinians were injured by live fire and 15 others were injured by rubber-coated metal bullets and tear gas inhalation. Qassas was evacuated by ambulance to a hospital, where he was pronounced dead.

Shot by soldiers while throwing stones at the Eyal checkpoint along with several other teens. According to Palestinian paramedics who evacuated him, deceased, about 15 minutes after the shooting, the soldiers provided no care.

Run over and injured by a Palestinian along with 18 other Israelis while standing at a bus stop at an intersection. Two of the victims were seriously injured, and six were moderately injured. The driver continued driving and hit a police car at a nearby intersection before being fatally shot by police officers.

Fatally shot by police officers after hitting a police car with the car he was driving. Earlier, Zyud ran over 19 Israelis who were waiting at a nearby bus stop and injured them. One of the victims died of her wounds about a week later. According to the police, after hitting the police car, Zyud stepped out of the vehicle holding a screwdriver and was then shot. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot in the bedroom by soldiers who raided his family home. Before shooting Sanajrah, the soldiers gathered the rest of his family in another room in the house, attacked them, threatened them, and ransacked their home. Sanajrah was an al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed by shots fired by undercover Border Police officers while participating in clashes that broke out after the officers raided the eastern part of the city. Shots were fired at the officers during the clashes. Later that day, undercover Border Police officers killed another Palestinian during a fire exchange that developed after they surrounded the house where he had barricaded himself, according to the police, to arrest him, as part of Operation Iron Wall. According to the police, the forces arrested three Palestinians at the scene.

Killed by live fire and a shoulder missile fired at the house in which he was barricaded during a fire exchange between him and undercover Border Police officers, who, the police claimed, had arrived to arrest him. The incident took place during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Another Palestinian was killed by Israeli forces fire, while participating in clashes in which Palestinians fired at the Israeli forces near the house. According to the police, the forces arrested three Palestinians at the scene. Sadiyah was a senior Hamas military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot by soldiers. The military initially claimed that the soldiers shot Kilani after he fired at them, and later admitted that Kilani had no firearms, claiming instead he had advanced toward the checkpoint armed with a knife. Israel is holding his body.

Injured in the head after soldiers in an armored military vehicle collided with the motorcycle he was riding during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Security camera footage shows the military vehicle speeding into the traffic circle and hitting Salahs motorcycle, which was already inside it. The force of the impact threw Salah off the motorcycle, which continued moving. Another military vehicle stopped near Salah for a few seconds before driving on. Salah was taken by car to a hospital, where he was pronounced dead.

Killed when Israeli forces, including Special Police Unit, military and Shin Bet personnel, threw a grenade into her remote homes yard, while she stepped out to listen to the muazzins call for dawn prayer. The forces then raided the house and detained her husband, two sons, and two grandchildren, ages seven and 13. The incident occurred during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. Abu Ghalis husband and two grandchildren were held for several hours in the Jalameh military camp and then released. Her body was handed over to the Red Crescent later that day. Over the course of the day, the Israeli forces killed three more Palestinians in the city.

Killed in a fire exchange with Special Police Unit officers who surrounded the house where he was barricaded in the eastern neighborhood of the city during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. During the operation, the Israeli forces killed another Palestinian who came out of a nearby house and claimed they wounded another. On the same day, forces made up of Special Police Unit, military and Shin Bet personnel killed two more Palestinians in the city, including a woman. Abu Dawas was a senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed in a fire exchange with soldiers and Special Police Unit officers who raided the neighborhood of Khallet a-Soha in the southern part of the city during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. On the same day, Israeli forces killed three more people in the eastern part of the city, including a woman. Abu 'Obeid was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Shot by Special Police Unit officers who surrounded a nearby house as he went from his home to a nearby grocery store to buy groceries for the Suhur meal (before the Ramadan fast), during Operation Iron Wall in the northern West Bank. In the house they surrounded, the officers killed another Palestinian and, according to the police, wounded another. The police left Abu Ghalis body on the street for about four hours and placed the body of the second Palestinian next to it. The two bodies were then loaded onto a military bulldozer and taken away. The family members, who watched the events from the window of their second-floor home, were unable to approach him due to the shooting and the presence of Israeli armed forces. On the same day, forces made up of Special Police Unit, military and Shin Bet personnel killed two more Palestinians in the city, including a woman. Israel is holding his body.

Shot in the head by soldiers who entered and patrolled the town in a military jeep. Shtayeh and his cousin, a minor, who were inside a grocery store, stepped out to flee the scene when they noticed a jeep approaching and youths throwing stones at it, but soldiers fatally shot him before they were able to escape.

Wounded by soldier gunfire while standing outside a cafe eating a sandwich. The soldiers then also fired at two Palestinians who tried to help the injured Qatuni into the cafe, wounding one of them, then vandalized the cafe, handcuffed the owner and customers, stole money from them, and finally detained one customer. Israel is holding his body.

Injured by police gunfire when he tried to escape a cafe with dozens of other youths after the police arrived in unmarked vehicles and opened a barrage of fire on the compound without any warning. The police then handcuffed those who were unable to escape and detained two of them. At least two more Palestinians were injured by police fire. Quran was taken by car to a hospital, where he was pronounced dead.

Killed at the end of a fire exchange with Special Police Unit officers and soldiers who surrounded the house where he was barricaded. The forces fired shoulder missiles at the house and activated an explosive drone. Yusef was a Hamas military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Critically wounded by shots fired by a police officer after entering a police checkpoint in a commercial vehicle with Israeli license plates, and, according to the police, failing to obey the officers directions, fleeing, and attempting to run over the shooting officer. The police also said he had earlier attempted to run over another police officer near Mishor Adumim. Abu Hamad was taken to an Israeli hospital and died of his wounds shortly after. Israel held his body until 17 June 2025.
Fatally shot by soldiers in ambush while throwing rocks at Route 60 near the village. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot during a fire exchange with undercover Border Police officers who surrounded the building he was in. The police claimed Suliman was shot while trying to flee the scene. Israel is holding his body.

Shot in the thigh by soldiers who blew up the doors of his familys apartment and his uncles apartment, saying they were looking for his brother Yusef. When Khamash began climbing the stairs to his parents' room, the soldiers shot him from behind and left him bleeding in the apartment. The soldiers then took Khamashs body out to the street, apparently, after attempting to administer first aid, and handed it over to the Red Crescent. The soldiers then arrested Khamashs brother, Yusef, and another Palestinian.

Shot in the back by soldiers at the entrance to town. Zyud and other young men threw stones and IEDs at two armored military vehicles that entered the town, and the soldiers fired at them from a machine gun mounted on one of them and left the scene a few minutes later. Two more minors were injured by soldiers' gunfire at the scene, and another Palestinian was injured by gunfire during clashes that developed in another neighborhood in the town. Zyud was taken by ambulance to Ibn Sina Hospital in the city of Jenin, where he was pronounced dead.

Fatally shot by soldiers, according to the military, while throwing stones at Route 375, along with another Palestinian, who was injured. The photo released by the military shows Zauls mutilated body. Israel is holding his body.

Shot in the side of the body by soldiers who ambushed him near his home when he returned there after fleeing with his son to avoid arrest during the military raid. His body was handed over to the Palestinian Red Crescent about two and a half hours after the shooting, with dark marks on his neck, possibly indicating strangulation by hand rope. Signs of head trauma were also observed, but a medical report cites a bullet wound as the cause of death.
Fatally shot by soldiers at Haris Junction (Gitay Avisar Junction). The military claimed she threw stones at cars on the road and a knife was found on her body. Israel is holding her body.

Shot in the abdomen by soldiers on a balcony on the second floor of a building on the main street in the camp, as he tried to escape with other youths from two military jeeps after some youths threw stones at them. A woman in a nearby house tried to rescue Hattab but was forced to return home because of the shooting. Two more Palestinians were wounded by the soldiers fire, including a minor. Hattab was taken to al-Istishari Hospital in the city of Ramallah where he underwent surgery, but after several hours, the doctors were forced to pronounce him dead.

Fatally shot along with another Palestinian in a fire exchange with soldiers and Special Police Unit officers who surrounded the cave in which they barricaded themselves and fired shoulder missiles at it, as part of a targeted killing aimed at him. Another Palestinian who was with them in the cave was arrested by the forces, and then a military bulldozer destroyed the cave. Zakarnah was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot along with Muhammad Zakarnah in a fire exchange with soldiers and Special Police Unit officers who surrounded the cave in which they barricaded themselves and fired shoulder missiles at it, as part of the targeted killing of Muhammad Zakarneh. Another Palestinian who was with them in the cave was arrested by the forces, and then a military bulldozer destroyed the cave. Khzeimiyah was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.
Fatally shot by soldiers in ambush along with another Palestinian, while the two were throwing stones at Route 505. A third Palestinian who was with them was unharmed. Israel is holding his body.
Fatally shot by soldiers in ambush along with a Palestinian minor, while the two were throwing stones at Route 505. A third Palestinian who was with them was unharmed. Israel is holding his body.
Fatally shot by soldiers at a checkpoint after firing at them using a makeshift weapon. Israel is holding his body.

Shot by soldiers who raided a house in the southern neighborhood of the town, while throwing stones at the house along with other minors from a distance of about 50 meters. Taken by car to the clinic in town and then by ambulance to a hospital in the city of Jenin, where he was pronounced dead.

Shot in the chest after closing his family's grocery store when military jeeps were reported in the village. Soldiers who got out of the jeeps approached the grocery store under cover of a grove and shot him from a distance of about 50 meters immediately after he stepped out. When some young men tried to evacuate him, the soldiers ordered them to back away, and allowed his evacuation only after trying unsuccessfully to provide first aid, but then blocked the path of the car in which he was being evacuated, forcing the driver to take a detour. Abd al-Khaleq was pronounced dead in a hospital in Nablus.

Shot by soldiers who got out of military jeeps after he threw stones at them during their retreat from the town after a raid and curfew that lasted about two days. In footage posted on social media, soldiers are seen exiting the jeep and firing. After Khdeir was injured, the soldiers called an ambulance that was parked about 100 meters away to evacuate him. Died of his wounds shortly after.

Fatally shot by soldiers who raided his extended family's residential building after he refused to turn himself in and the soldiers ordered the family members to leave.. Undercover officers entered the building, followed by uniformed soldiers. The soldiers attacked two of Abu Leils brothers, used them as human shields, and forced them to enter the building several times and retrieve drones the military had sent into it. The soldiers also forced his sister to sit on the steps of the building and serve as a human shield. According to the military, a gun was found in Abu Leils car during the operation. Abu Leil was a senior al-Aqsa Martyrs Brigade operative. Israel is holding his body.

Shot by soldiers who were stopping a car at the al-Fahs checkpoint at the southern entrance to the city of Hebron, after running over a soldier and, according to media reports, moderately injuring him. Hreibat got out of the car, tried to advance towards the soldiers with a knife in his hand, and was then shot. The military notified the Palestinian DCO of his death several hours later. Israel is holding his body.

Member of the Palestinian Authority security forces. Fatally shot by undercover Border Police officers while waiting for his father near a neighborhood barbershop and talking to another youth, who was injured and fled. The police claimed that al-Kukhun was armed and posed a danger to the forces. However, B'Tselem's investigation shows that he carried a weapon as part of his duties and that he surrendered as soon as the undercover officers fired at him, raising his hands and posing a danger to no one. The officers entered the barbershop, handcuffed the customers, severely beat one of them, arrested him, and confiscated the security camera recording device and other equipment. Israel is holding his body.

Killed along with another Palestinian during a fire exchange with Special Police Unit officers, soldiers, and Shin Bet personnel who surrounded a house under construction where they were hiding. Video footage released by the military shows an explosion in the house. Al-Bitawi was a senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed along with another Palestinian during a fire exchange with Special Police Unit officers, soldiers, and Shin Bet personnel who surrounded a house under construction where they were hiding. Video footage released by the military shows an explosion in the house. 'Abd a-Nabi was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Critically injured by shots fired by a Palestinian in ambush at the car in which she and her husband, who was lightly injured, were traveling on Route 446. Gez, who was in the advanced stages of pregnancy, was taken to the hospital, where physicians performed a cesarean section. She was pronounced dead the next day. Her infant son died two weeks later.

Died at 15 days old, after being delivered by caesarean section performed while his mother was being resuscitated. The mother and father were shot by a Palestinian in ambush while driving on Route 446. His mother, who was critically injured, was pronounced dead the next day at the hospital. His father was lightly injured.

Killed along with four other Palestinians, including a minor, during a fire exchange with soldiers who raided the town, surrounded the three-story building in which they had barricaded themselves and fired shoulder-fired missiles at it. During the operation, the Israeli forces destroyed a significant portion of the building, rendering it uninhabitable. At the end of the operation, a military bulldozer scooped Bani Odehs body and three others into its bucket and drove with them in it through the streets of the town and nearby communities. According to the military, four Palestinians were arrested in the town and the nearby city of Tubas during the raid. Bani Odeh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed along with four other Palestinians, including a minor, during a fire exchange with soldiers who raided the town, surrounded the three-story building in which they had barricaded themselves and fired shoulder-fired missiles at it. During the operation, the Israeli forces destroyed a significant portion of the building, rendering it uninhabitable. At the end of the operation, a military bulldozer scooped Bani Odehs body and three others into its bucket and drove with them in it through the streets of the town and nearby communities. According to the military, four Palestinians were arrested in the town and the nearby city of Tubas during the raid. Bani 'Odeh was a Hamas military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed along with four other Palestinians, during a fire exchange with soldiers who raided the town, surrounded the three-story building in which they had barricaded themselves and fired shoulder-fired missiles at it. During the operation, the Israeli forces destroyed a significant portion of the building, rendering it uninhabitable. At the end of the operation, a military bulldozer scooped Bani Odehs body and three others into its bucket and drove with them in it through the streets of the town and nearby communities. According to the military, four Palestinians were arrested in the town and the nearby city of Tubas during the raid. Bani Odeh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed along with four other Palestinians, including a minor, during a fire exchange with soldiers who raided the town, surrounded the three-story building in which they had barricaded themselves and fired shoulder-fired missiles at it. During the operation, the Israeli forces destroyed a significant portion of the building, rendering it uninhabitable. At the end of the operation, a military bulldozer scooped Bani Odehs body and three others into its bucket and drove with them in it through the streets of the town and nearby communities. According to the military, four Palestinians were arrested in the town and the nearby city of Tubas during the raid. Bani Odeh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed along with four other Palestinians, including a minor, during a fire exchange with soldiers who raided the town, surrounded the three-story building in which they had barricaded themselves and fired shoulder-fired missiles at it. During the operation, the Israeli forces destroyed a significant portion of the building, rendering it uninhabitable. At the end of the operation, a military bulldozer scooped the bodies of the other four into its bucket and drove with them in it through the streets of the town and nearby communities. Bsharats charred body was found by residents in the rubble of the building. According to the military, four Palestinians were arrested in the town and the nearby city of Tubas during the raid. Bsharat was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Shot by Israel Police officers at Bab al-Silsila (the Gate of the Chain in Temple Mount) in the Old City of Jerusalem. The police claimed he was shot after stabbing and moderately wounding a police officer. Israel is holding his body.

Shot by soldiers from an ambush while throwing stones on Highway 60 along with two other minors who were injured, fled, and were evacuated by local residents to ambulances waiting in the nearby village of Asirah a-Shamaliyah, which took them to a hospital in the city of Nablus. Locals searching for a-Shaghnubi were unable to get close due to the presence of soldiers, who fired in the air and prevented his evacuation by ambulance. About two hours after the shooting, the Palestinian DCO was informed that a-Shaghnubi had died of his wounds. Israel is holding his body.

Shot by soldiers who handcuffed him, blindfolded him, and took him out of his house. According to the military, Samarah ran towards them while holding a bag that was suspected as carrying explosives. His father, who saw the soldiers leading him behind the house, heard several shots and his wife, who was detained in the yard, heard him screaming. During the Israeli raid on the town, the death of a woman from a nearby settlement who was shot in her car by a Palestinian, soldiers attacked Samarah's relatives, including his uncle and his two sons, severely beating one of them. The military imposed a full blockade on the town for about nine days, took over houses, damaged property, and allowed settlers to riot against the residents.

Shot by Israeli forces who surrounded a house belonging to his relatives to arrest a family member who was not present. Jalaytah and other youths threw stones at the forces, who fired at them, wounding him. He was taken to a hospital in the city, where he died of his wounds shortly after.

Shot in the neck by soldiers sitting in a military jeep, from a distance of about 50 meters, as military, Border Police, and Israeli Forces withdrew from the city after raiding its gold market. During the retreat, youths threw stones at the forces, who fired tear gas grenades at them. Kharaz was sitting in front of his shop in the al-Qadumi Market, about 250 meters from the gold market, with other shopkeepers. When the jeep stopped in front of them and its door opened, Kharaz and the others ran down nearby stairs, but the soldier managed to shoot and hit Kharaz. Residents helped him stand on his feet, climb up the stairs, and enter an ambulance that was waiting there. He was taken to a hospital, where doctors tried unsuccessfully to resuscitate him and had to pronounce him dead.

Shot in the abdomen while asleep in his bed by soldiers who broke down the door of his house and entered the room where he was sleeping. The soldiers took his body and handed it over to the Red Crescent two hours later. The IDF Spokesperson told the media that the incident was being investigated.

Shot by soldiers in ambush in farm fields near Rotue 5056, and evacuated in a military vehicle from which he was transferred to an Israeli ambulance. After the shooting, soldiers raided a house overlooking the spot where the shooting took place, viewed the security camera footage, and then deleted it. According to the military, Fuqaha tried to throw stones at the road. However, according to the witness with the security cameras, the footage showed he did not hold or throw any stones. Israel is holding his body.

Shot in the head by soldiers from a nearby grove while trying to cross the separation fence to work in Israel along with two other Palestinians, who were injured, one of them seriously. The three were evacuated by the Red Crescent to a hospital in Hebron, where Tlul was pronounced dead. The soldiers arrested about 10 other workers who tried to cross the fence and released them the next day.

An officer with the Palestinian Authority security forces. Shot by soldiers he fought off after they attacked him when he refused to take off his pants during a street search in the Old City of Nablus. His brother, Khaled 'Amirah, rushed to his aid and was also attacked by the soldiers. The soldiers dragged Khaled Amirah to an alley, pinned him down on the ground, choking him, and then tried to drag Nidal Amirah to the same alley. At that point, a volley of shots was fired in the alley, and some of the soldiers, as well as Nidal Amirah, fled back into the street, at which point the soldiers fatally shot Nidal Amirah. Seconds after, they fired a volley of shots at Khaled 'Amirah, who was still pinned down on the ground, killing him as well. The military claimed the brothers tried to snatch the weapon of one of the soldiers. Israel is holding his body.

Shot by soldiers while they were pinning him down to the ground in an alley in the Old City of Nablus, after he rushed to help his brother who was being attacked by the soldiers. The brother, Nidal Amirah, an officer with the Palestinian Authority security forces, had fought off soldiers who attacked him when he refused to take off his pants during a street search in the Old City of Nablus. Khaled Amirah rushed to his aid, and was also attacked by the soldiers, who dragged him to an alley, pinned him down on the ground, choked him, and then tried to drag his brother Nidal to the same alley. At that point, a volley of shots was fired in the alley, and some of the soldiers, as well as Nidal Amirah, fled back into the street, at which point the soldiers fatally shot Nidal Amirah. Seconds after, they fired a volley of shots at Khaled 'Amirah, who was still pinned down on the ground, killing him as well. The military claimed the brothers tried to snatch the weapon of one of the soldiers. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot by Special Police Unit officers and soldiers during a targeted killing aimed at him. Footage released by the police shows Bsharat running down the street, being shot and falling. A military jeep is then seen advancing towards him, and as soon as it reaches him, the video cuts off. During the operation, Israeli armed forces raided homes and arrested four Palestinians, one of whom was injured by the forces fire. Bsharat was a senior Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.
Fatally shot by soldiers at a checkpoint after, according to the military, arriving at the checkpoint and firing at them. Israel is holding his body.

Shot by soldiers on the balcony of a house under construction. According to B'Tselem's investigation, Hajajleh was sitting on the balcony with friends, smoking a hookah. When he went outside after hearing a noise, he saw the soldiers violently leading his uncle down the street. He argued with the soldiers and they assaulted him, beating al-Hajajleh and his friends, and then took him to the balcony, where they shot him. The military claimed the soldiers shot him after he tried to stab them and snatch a weapon from one of them. His friends testified they heard him screaming and groaning and shortly afterwards the shooting.

Shot in the neck during a joint attack on the town by dozens of settlers and two soldiers, as he bent down to pick up a stone in an attempt to repel them. Earlier, settlers set fire to the town's fields. His brother, who threw stones at the shooting settler, was shot in the pelvis by a soldier and seriously injured. The two were evacuated to a clinic in Surif and from there to the government hospital in Hebron, where Muhammad was pronounced dead. During the attack, their 85-year-old father and another relative were injured by stones thrown by settlers, and a soldier kicked another brother in the face.

Shot in the back by soldiers after he threw a stone at an armored vehicle coming from the direction of Route 449. His friend, a minor, who was with him fled the scene after seeing Hamayel fall. Hamayel was evacuated, deceased, in a Palestinian ambulance that arrived at the scene following coordination with the DCO, and pronounced dead at a hospital in the city of Ramallah.

Shot in the head at his doorstep from a distance of 15 meters by soldiers who were chasing youths who had repelled a settler attack on the village. Hamayel had eariler helped put out fires in houses and cars torched by settlers. The soldiers prevented a young man from evacuating for several minutes, threatening him at gunpoint. Hamayel was taken by car to a hospital in Ramallah, where he was pronounced dead. During the settler and soldier attack on the village, soldiers fatally shot two other residents and wounded 12. The settlers injured residents with stones, burned down three cars and set fire to three homes, which were partially burned.

Shot from a distance of about 40 meters by soldiers, as he was running away from them into the village after he and other youths repelled settlers who attacked the village. Taken by car to a hospital in Ramallah, where he was pronounced dead. During the settler and soldier attack on the village, soldiers fatally shot two other residents and wounded 12. The settlers injured residents with stones, burned down three cars and set fire to three homes, which were partially burned.

Shot by soldiers, as he was running away from them into the village after he and other youths repelled settlers who attacked the village. Taken by car to a hospital in Ramallah, where he was pronounced dead. During the settler and soldier attack on the village, soldiers fatally shot two other residents and wounded 12. The settlers injured residents with stones and set fire to three homes, that were partially burned and three cars that were completely burned.

Shot by soldiers who climbed onto the roof of a building in the center of the town during clashes that developed after they entered and surrounded a house to arrest a Palestinian. During the clashes, Palestinians threw stones and IEDs at the soldiers. Hushiyeh was trying to cross the road on his way home with his cousin, a minor, when he was shot by the soldiers. He was taken by residents to a nearby ambulance and then to a clinic in the town, where he was pronounced dead.

Shot in the head by an officer with the Border Police undercover unit from a distance of about 50 meters, as Border Police forces that had raided the camp were retreating. Judah was sitting on the roof of her fourth-floor house with about 20 of her grandchildren, most of them minors. According to the police, the officer fired during a violent disturbance in which another officer was hit on the head by a rock. According to the family, no stones were thrown from the roof. Her body was evacuated by an Israeli ambulance, and soldiers at the checkpoint refused to allow family members to accompany her in their cars. The body was returned to the family that evening.

Shot by soldiers after he climbed a ladder and started crossing the Separation Barrier to reach his job in Israel. About 20 workers who came with him fled after hearing the gunfire. His body was handed over to the Red Crescent at the a-Dhahiriyah/Meitar Checkpoint about two hours after the shooting.

Shot by soldiers while participating in clashes at Manara Square in the city center, in which youths threw stones and fired fireworks at the soldiers. The clashes broke out after military and police counterterrorism (Yamam) forces raided a house on a nearby street, interrogated a Palestinian and arrested him. Afterwards, the forces raided another house in the Ein Musbah neighborhood in the northwest of the city and arrested four Palestinian citizens of Israel who had fled to Ramallah on criminal grounds. Evacuated by ambulance to a hospital in the city, where he was pronounced dead.

Injured by soldiers' gunfire while riding home on an electric bicycle from the city of Tulkarm to the eastern part of the camp where his family was staying after being displaced from Tulkarm Refugee Camp about six months earlier. After he was shot, two soldiers approached him and administered first aid, and about ten minutes later he was evacuated by ambulance to Thabet Thabet Hospital in the city of Tulkarm, where he was pronounced dead. His son and neighbor approached the site to get him out but had to turn back due to the presence of the soldiers, who were joined by about ten more. The soldiers confiscated his bicycle, wallet and other belongings he had with him.

Shot by soldiers after going towards his relative, Wisam Shtayeh, who had been shot dead by soldiers trying to arrest him and surrounding Nassar's uncle's house. Nassar had earlier jumped over the fence between his home and his uncles house after seeing his uncle, who had come outside after hearing noises, shot and injured by the soldiers.

Shot by soldiers while fleeing his in-laws house towards a nearby olive grove, after they surrounded the house in order to arrest him and called out for him to surrender. After he was shot, a relative went towards him and was also shot dead by the soldiers. His father-in-law was shot and injured in the leg by soldiers when he came out of the house after hearing noise outside, and was taken to a hospital in Nablus. According to the military, Shtayeh was a major weapons dealer in the town, and a handgun and bullet magazines were found in his confiscated car. Israel is holding his body.

Injured by soldiers' gunfire together with two other minors while throwing stones during the withdrawal of Israeli forces from Nablus. Taken by private car to Rafidiya Hospital in the city, where he died of his wounds about three days later. Two other minors were injured by the soldiers' gunfire.

Critically injured when stabbed and shot by two Palestinians who arrived in a car with an Israeli license plate at the Haharim mall complex and seized his weapon. The two Palestinians were shot dead in an exchange of fire with soldiers and armed Israeli civilians on site. Pronounced dead shortly afterwards.

Had a neurological illness. Shot dead by soldiers who entered houses near his in the western neighborhood of the village, after he came out of his home when he saw soldiers raiding his brothers house, approached them and stabbed a soldier, who according to the military was moderately injured. Two military jeeps ran over al-'Amurs body, according to eyewitnesses at least twice. After the shooting, the soldiers raided the family's homes, ransacked them and severely assaulted his relatives. The soldiers arrested at least ten Palestinians, nine of whom were released after a few hours. Israel is holding his body.

A Palestinian Authority police officer. Shot by soldiers and armed Israeli civilians along with another PA officer during an exchange of fire in the parking lot of the Haharim mall complex. The two officers had arrived at the complex in a car with an Israeli license plate, stabbed a security guard near the mall, seized his weapon and shot and killed him. Pronounced dead shortly afterwards. Israel is holding his body.

A Palestinian Authority police officer. Shot by soldiers and armed Israeli civilians along with another PA officer during an exchange of fire in the parking lot of the Haharim mall complex. The two officers had arrived at the complex in a car with an Israeli license plate, stabbed a security guard near the mall, seized his weapon and shot and killed him. Pronounced dead shortly afterwards. Israel is holding his body.

Shot in the back by an Israeli in civilian clothing while running away, together with other youths, from settlers who had arrived in cars from Route 60 and were chasing them, after they had reached the outpost settlers established on land belonging to al-Mazraah a-Sharqiyah. The youths could not carry him and continued running. His body was found by residents who were searching for him after learning he had been missing for hours. Residents of Sinjil and al-Mazraah a-Sharqiyah tried to reach their land in the al-Baten area to work it and make a show of presence. Clashes broke out between the residents and settlers, and a military force arrived at the site after Shalabi was shot, firing tear gas canisters and live rounds in the air. Dozens of Palestinians were injured by the settlers, who beat them and threw stones at them. According to the military, two settlers were lightly injured. According to media reports, a reservist soldier was arrested on suspicion of the shooting.
Shot dead by soldiers, according to the military after he was near an outpost while armed. Israel is holding his body.

Shot by Israeli forces surrounding his house. After he was injured, they arrested him and prevented a Palestinian ambulance from evacuating him. A few hours later, the Palestinian DCO informed his family he had died of his wounds. He was an operative in the al-Far'ah Brigade. Israel is holding his body.

Shot by soldiers who got out of two military vehicles that entered the northern part of the town. Qabha, who was walking along the street, tried to escape when he noticed the soldiers, who called on him to stop, and they began shooting at him. His father arrived and approached him, and soldiers assaulted him, tied his hands, and seated him next to his dying son. For about half an hour, the soldiers prevented an ambulance at the site from evacuating him. Pronounced dead at a medical center in the town.

Shot by soldiers who raided a house at the entrance to the town. Naser and two other minors threw stones at the military jeep parked near the house. He was shot and injured and fled into an olive grove, where he fell down. He was taken by paramedics to a hospital in Jenin, where he was pronounced dead. The two other minors fled the site. CCTV footage shows soldiers chasing the youths and firing.

Shot and injured in the thigh by Israeli forces who raided the city of Nablus for about twenty hours to arrest a Palestinian, while he was standing in an alley at the entrance to the camp together with his cousin, a minor. A military, Border Police and Shin Bet force raided a house in the city, detonated explosives nearby and arrested its owner. The forces raided the Rafidiya and al-Arabi hospitals searching for the wanted man, who was later arrested. During the raid, clashes broke out in various parts of the city, in which Palestinians threw stones at the forces. While a military jeep and a Border Police jeep were driving, forces fired at people standing at the camp entrance, injuring Mabruk and another Palestinian. A resident carried him on foot to an ambulance waiting nearby. Died of his wounds about three days later at al-Arabi Hospital.

Shot by soldiers while standing on a hill together with four other teens and throwing stones at military vehicles withdrawing from the nearby town of Qabatiyah. Soldiers got out of the vehicles, chased the teens through olive groves and fired at them. The other boys fled toward the town. About an hour after the shooting, paramedics arrived at the site and the soldiers directed them to Hamrans body. They took him to a hospital, where he was pronounced dead.

Shot dead by soldiers along with another minor near the Separation Barrier, according to the military after they threw Molotov cocktails at Route 60. In a video published on social media, an ambulance is seen at the site and gunfire is heard. Israel is holding his body.

Shot dead by soldiers along with another minor near the Separation Barrier, according to the military after they threw Molotov cocktails at Route 60. In a video published on social media, an ambulance is seen at the site and gunfire is heard. Israel is holding his body.
Shot by the settlement guard, according to the military after he threw stones and ran toward the settlement gate armed with a knife. Israel is holding his body.

Shot by a soldier, according to the military after he tried to carry out a stabbing attack near the settlement. In CCTV footage published in the media, Samamrah is seen running away from the site, and then the soldier fires. Israel is holding his body.

Shot in the chest by a settler who opened fire at village residents who had gathered after an excavator worked their land, while al-Hazalin was filming him. The settler had earlier hit a resident with his handgun during an altercation bewteen him and residents. The excavator driver, who drove through one of the groves, hit another resident on the head with the excavator's hammer after at least one stone was thrown at the excavator's protective cage. Residents and activists carried al-Hazalin to the nearby settlement of Carmel. There, they encountered the settler who shot him, and he slapped al-Hazalins mother and knocked her to the ground. Al-Hazalin was taken by Israeli ambulance to Soroka Hospital, where he was pronounced dead. Israel held his body until 7 August 2025.

Shot by soldiers, who claimed they opened fire after he threw a stone at them while they were operating in the Ras al-Jura neighborhood at the northern entrance to the city. Israel is holding his body.

Shot in the back by settlers who were trying to kick out Palestinian farmers from a field where he was working in the south of the town and advance towards the towns home, in the presence of soldiers. After a settler pushed a Palestinian and knocked down his phone, one of the farmers threw a stone at the settlers, who opened fire, injuring Asfar and six other residents. The injured were driven to a clinic in the town and from there to the Rafidya Hospital, in Nablus, where he was pronounced dead. After the settlers opened fire, the soldiers fired tear gas canisters and live rounds at the Palestinian residents and allowed the settlers to leave the area without detaining any of them. Some of the soldiers then left in the settlers ATVs.

Killed in a fire exchange with Special Police Unit officers who surrounded an agricultural building where he was staying along with another Palestinian, who was injured and arrested. The officers fired live rounds and shoulder-fired missiles at the building, then demolished it with a bulldozer while Amer was still inside. The military claimed he was armed and tried to flee. His charred body was discovered by residents under the ruins of the building. Amer was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative.

Shot in the thigh by a settler, according to the military a soldier on leave, who was providing security for works to build a new outpost on land privately owned by village residents, after throwing a stone at him. About 25 residents were protesting the establishment of the outpost and an earlier settler attack on a Palestinian teen. The settler fired in the air and at the ground, and then, after Dawabsheh threw a stone at him, which did not hit, shot directly at Dawabsheh and fired at the other protesters. The military claimed the protestors tried to snatch his firearm and asoldier and a civilian were injured by stone-throwing. B'Tselem's investigation refutes this. The protesters knocked down the settler in an attempt to neutralize him while he was shooting and backed off when uniformed soldiers approached the scene while firing in the air. Dawabsheh was driven in a private car to the village clinic and from there to Rafidya Hospital in Nablus, where he was pronounced dead.

Shot by soldiers while ambushing military jeeps with a Molotov cocktail in his hand. Soldiers raided the town following clashes between local residents and settlers, who invaded the fields between the town and the nearby village of Khirbet Abu Falah a few hours earlier and set fire to a car, agricultural structures, and fields. The soldiers prevented access to Abu Alia for about 15 minutes, and only after they left the scene was he evacuated by residents to the clinic in Abu Falah and from there to a hospital in the city of Ramallah, where he was pronounced dead.

Shot by soldiers in the Tel Rumeidah neighborhood, according to the military, after pulling a gun at soldiers staffing a military post. It later turned out to be an air gun. Al-Idah was arrested and taken to Shaare Zedek Medical Center in Israel, where he died of his wounds. Israel is holding his body.

Shot in the shoulder and back by soldiers, when he threw stones at them from his rooftop after the soldiers had raided his neighbors home and arrested him. Madni climbed onto the roof after hearing an explosion from the neighbor's house. He was taken by car to Rafidya Hospital in Nablus, where he died of his wounds shortly after.

Shot in the head, chest, abdomen, armpit, arm, and leg by soldiers who ordered him to get out of his car at the al-Murabaah checkpoint. According to the military, he threw a suspicious object at the soldiers and did not obey their instructions. In video footage posted on social media, Shhadeh is seen standing in front of the soldiers, and two of them fire more than 10 shots at him, including after he falls. One of his sons arrived at the checkpoint, but the soldiers did not allow him to approach his fathers body. His body was handed over to the Red Crescent two hours later. Shhadeh had been driving to Tell to go shopping.

Fatally shot by two armed Palestinians who fired at a bus stop and two buses that were stuck in traffic in the Ramot intersection. Five other Israelis were fatally shot and 28 others were injured by gunfire or broken glass, four of whom sustained severe injuries. The two Palestinian were fatally shot by an Israeli soldier and an armed Israeli civilian.

Fatally shot by two armed Palestinians who fired at a bus stop and two buses that were stuck in traffic in the Ramot intersection. Five other Israelis, including a woman, were fatally shot and 28 others were injured by gunfire or broken glass, four of whom sustained severe injuries. The two Palestinian were fatally shot by an Israeli soldier and an armed Israeli civilian.

Fatally shot by two armed Palestinians who fired at a bus stop and two buses that were stuck in traffic in the Ramot intersection. Five other Israelis, including a woman, were fatally shot and 28 others were injured by gunfire or broken glass, four of whom sustained severe injuries. The two Palestinian were fatally shot by an Israeli soldier and an armed Israeli civilian.

Fatally shot by two armed Palestinians who fired at a bus stop and two buses that were stuck in traffic in the Ramot intersection. Five other Israelis, including a woman, were fatally shot and 28 others were injured by gunfire or broken glass, four of whom sustained severe injuries. The two Palestinian were fatally shot by an Israeli soldier and an armed Israeli civilian.

Fatally shot by two armed Palestinians who fired at a bus stop and two buses that were stuck in traffic in the Ramot intersection. Five other Israelis, including a woman, were fatally shot and 28 others were injured by gunfire or broken glass, four of whom sustained severe injuries. The two Palestinian were fatally shot by an Israeli soldier and an armed Israeli civilian.

Fatally shot by two armed Palestinians who fired at a bus stop and two buses that were stuck in traffic in the Ramot intersection. Five other Israelis, including a woman, were fatally shot and 28 others were injured by gunfire or broken glass, four of whom sustained severe injuries. The two Palestinian were fatally shot by an Israeli soldier and an armed Israeli civilian.

Shot by soldiers after he and other relatives visited the ruins of their homes that had been destroyed by the military, believing the military raid on the camp, carried out as part of Operation Iron Walls, which had been underway since January, had ended. As they tried to leave the area, a military vehicle pulled up, and the soldiers fired at them from a distance of about 50 meters. The military claimed the soldiers fired at suspects who posed a threat. Evacuated to a government hospital in the city of Jenin, where he was pronounced dead. Another minor was killed and two other Palestinians were injured by the soldiers' gunfire.

Shot by soldiers near a roadblock the military had placed near Ibn Sina Hospital to separate the refugee camp from the city of Jenin, while he and other boys were watching camp residents who were trying to return to their homes. The residents tried to visit the site believing the military raid on the camp, carried out as part of Operation Iron Walls, which had been underway since January, had ended. The military claimed the soldiers fired at suspects who posed a threat. Evacuated by local residents, on foot, to Ibn Sina Hospital, where he was pronounced dead. Another minor was killed and two other Palestinians were injured by the soldiers' gunfire.

Fatally shot by an Israeli soldier and an Israeli armed civilian along with another Palestinian after the two had fired at a bus stop and two buses that were stuck in traffic in the Ramot intersection, killing six Israeli civilians and wounding 28, for of them severely. Amru was a Hamas military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot by an Israeli soldier and an Israeli armed civilian along with another Palestinian after the two had fired at a bus stop and two buses that were stuck in traffic in the Ramot intersection, killing six Israeli civilians and wounding 28, for of them severely. Taha was a Hamas military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Shot by soldiers along with two friends, who were injured, after they placed obstacles on a road built by settlers and leading to an outpost they established on village land. The two friends escaped and were taken by car to the center of the village, where they were transferred to an ambulance. On the way, the ambulance was detained near the settler-built road by soldiers who demanded one of the wounded men be taken out. They withdrew the demand after an argument, and led the ambulance driver to Abu Alawi, who lay wounded in the ground, with tourniquets on his legs, so that he could evacuate him as well. The three were taken to a hospital in Ramallah, where Abu Alawi died of his wounds the next day.

Fatally shot along with a Palestinian citizen of Israel by police officers with the Gidonim Unit, soldiers, and Shin Bet personnel, who arrived at the scene in a private car and fired at them as they were loading furniture onto a truck in the middle of the night. Three Palestinians who were with them were arrested and released the next day. The military claimed the two were trafficking in firearms and a rifle was found in the truck. The Palestinian DCO learned of their deaths in the morning hours of that day. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot by Border Police officers after crossing the separation fence in a-Ram using a ladder and rope, along with other Palestinians who were waiting to cross after him, to work in Israel. His body was handed over to the Red Crescent that day.

Shot by a settler, according to the military a soldier on leave,who was grazing sheep with another settler near a playground where Naasans children were playing in the southern part of the village. The children fled, while Naasan and other men managed to drive away one of the settlers, but the other refused to leave. During the confrontation that developed, in which the young men tried to drive him away by throwing stones, he fired at them. He first hit a young man hiding behind a portable toilet, injuring him in the thigh, and then Naasan, who fell to the ground. The settler continued firing at Naasan, and the young men, as Naasan was being evacuated. Naasan was taken by car to a hospital, where he was pronounced dead.

Shot by soldiers who entered the village in four military jeeps. The soldiers fired two shots in the air, and a confrontation ensued, during which Palestinian youths, including Barahmeh, threw stones at the armored jeeps. Some of the soldiers secretly took over a house in the center of the village and fired at Barahmeh from there. He was taken by ambulance to Khalil Suleiman Hospital in the city of Jenin, where he was pronounced dead. The military claimed Barahmeh threw explosive devices at the forces.

Killed along with another Palestinian in a greenhouse in agricultural fields in the east of the town. Military, Special Police Unit and Shin Bet forces raided the site, and a fire exchange with the two Palestinians ensued, during which the Israeli armed forces fired from machine guns and a launcher. According to the military, the two were planning to carry out an attack in the immediate future. Bani Odeh was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed along with another Palestinian in a greenhouse in agricultural fields in the east of the town. Military, Special Police Unit and Shin Bet forces raided the site, and a fire exchange with the two Palestinians ensued, during which the Israeli armed forces fired from machine guns and a launcher. According to the military, the two were planning to carry out an attack in the immediate future. Suliman was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.
Fatally shot by soldiers, according to the military, after carrying out a terrorist attack using a vehicle. Israel is holding his body.

Fatally shot by soldiers who fired dozens of bullets at his car, according to the army, after he tried to run over the soldiers at the checkpoint and fire at them. A friend who was traveling with him in the car was arrested. Israel is holding his body.

Wounded in the shoulder, back, and leg by soldiers' gunfire as he tried to escape with other young men after they had placed obstacles on a military road leading from the village to a military camp north of it and an outpost established between them. The young men tried to block the road after settlers who had come from that area attacked Palestinian cars on the road to Silwad. Three other young men were injured in the shooting, but they managed to escape. Three military jeeps arrived at the location where Ajaj fell, and about 20 minutes after the shooting, a Palestinian ambulance arrived at the scene, and a paramedic who evacuated him found a tourniquet on his leg but did not detect any signs of an attempt to treat the wounds in his upper body. He was taken to a hospital in Ramallah where he was pronounced dead.

Shot in the neck, stomach, and arm by soldiers, from a long distance, in the cinema square in the city center. Soldiers entered the city center and detained residents for inspection, and young people gathered in the area, shouting and throwing stones at them. After the soldiers left the area and the confrontation ended, Salamah was captured on a security camera crossing the square and falling to the ground. Fragments from the shooting wounded a Palestinian minor. Salamah was taken by ambulance to Khalil a-Suleiman Hospital in the city, where he was pronounced dead. The military claims Salamah threw an explosive device at the soldiers.

Wounded in the pelvis by shots fired by soldiers who got out of a military jeep after he fled with other boys and young men from the village high school yard, where they were playing soccer. The soldiers first fired tear gas grenades at the boys and young men, who then threw stones at the jeep from which the soldiers got out from a distance of several dozen meters. After fleeing, al-Halaq stopped in an elevated area overlooking the street where the soldiers were, about 200 meters away from them. One of the soldiers fired a live bullet at him and hit him. He managed to walk a few steps and then fell to the ground, bleeding. After the shooting, the soldiers threw several tear gas grenades at him, and when one of the youths tried to approach him, the soldiers fired several more shots at him, but he finally managed to approach al-Halaq him and pick him up. He carried him about 40 meters away, and from there, he was driven to the nearby al-Fawar Refugee Camp. Another car drove him to Abu al-Hassan al-Qassem Hospital in the town of Yatta. Died of his wounds at the hospital shortly after.

Shot by soldiers after throwing an IED at them during clashes that broke out after soldiers raided the town to arrest a Palestinian. Paramedics who arrived at the area were unable to reach him for about half an hour. He was taken to a hospital and died of his wounds shortly after.

Shot in the abdomen and leg while trying to close the door leading to the roof of his building, while he and his wife were hiding in the stairwell after hearing gunfire by Border Police officers who were raiding the neighborhood to arrest his nephew. The police delayed the arrival of the paramedics for about half an hour. After the paramedics finally managed to sneak in and then carried him on a blanket to an ambulance parked far from the house, they were held up again. In a video posted on social media, Border Police officers who were near the ambulance are seen dragging Dawood using the blanket he was lying on and attacking his sister-in-law who tried to prevent his abduction. The police dragged the dying Dawood to an alley where they stripped him and searched his person. Only about 15 minutes later, when he was apparently deceased, did they allow paramedics to take him to Rafidya Hospital in Nablus, where he was pronounced dead. The police claimed he was a threat to the forces.

Wounded in the chest by shots fired by a soldier from inside a military jeep that was traveling in a convoy of four jeeps exiting the camp. Security camera footage shows Abu Hanin leaning against a parked pickup truck on the street, with his hands empty, surrounded by about 20 residents, including children and young people who threw several objects at the armored jeeps. Abu Hanin was taken by residents on foot to an ambulance that was waiting about 150 meters away and took him to al-Arabi Hospital in the city of Nablus, where he died of his wounds the next day.
Fatally shot by Soldiers while trying to cross the separation barrier to work in Israel. His body was transferred to the Red Crescent, which transferred it to the government hospital in Hebron.

Killed along with two other Palestinians in a fire exchange with soldiers, Special Police Unit officers and Shin Bet personnel who surrounded the cave in which they barricaded themselves. Two were killed by light weapons and one by a missile fired from an aircraft. Alaqmah was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed along with two other Palestinians in a fire exchange with soldiers, Special Police Unit officers and Shin Bet personnel who surrounded the cave in which they barricaded themselves. Two were killed by light weapons and one by a missile fired from an aircraft. Jus was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Killed along with two other Palestinians in a fire exchange with soldiers, Special Police Unit officers and Shin Bet personnel who surrounded the cave in which they barricaded themselves. Two were killed by light weapons and one by a missile fired from an aircraft. Nashrati was an Islamic Jihad military wing operative. Israel is holding his body.

Wounded in the shoulder and chest by soldiers gunfire near a dirt mound barrier placed by the military at the southern entrance to the town on 7 October 2023. The soldiers prevented the ambulance from approaching the wounded man, and, after about 25 minutes, they allowed the crew to walk over to him and carry him to the ambulance. He was taken to a hospital in Ramallah where he was pronounced dead. A physician who examined his body said he had two fractures in his neck, indicating a twisting movement of the neck. The military claimed Hamed was shot after setting fire to a suspicious object.
